\par\par \b \uc2  WEDNESDAY AUGUST 29 2001,EDITORIALS OF INDONESIAN MAJOR DAILIES. \b0\par\par\uc2 811 \uc2 words\par \uc2 29 August 2001\par \uc2 ANTARA - The Indonesian National News Agency\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 Asia Pulse Pte Limited. Asia Pulse gives no warranty or guarantee as to the accuracy of the information, Asia Pulse shall not be liable for errors or omissions in, or delays or interruptions to or cessation of delivery of, the data through its negligence or otherwise.\par \par \uc2  FOLLY OF MILITARY OPTION Various statements from top government and Indonesian military officials about the problem of Aceh in the past week have confirmed our worst fear: The military option has once again been put on the front burner. Other option still available at the government's disposal, including the search for a negotiated settlement, have been put on hold while the military steps up its campaign against the armed Free Aceh Movement (GAM). The Coordinating Minister for Political and Security Affairs, retired Army General Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono said on Saturday that a new military operation would soon be launched in Aceh. Lt Gen Ryamizard Ryacudu, the chief of the Army Strategic \b \highlight22\uc2 Reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2  Command (Kostrad) set TNI's objective in such a campaign in no \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  terms: A total annihilation of GAM. The conflict between TNI and GAM has increased both in frequency and intensity in recent weeks. \par \par \uc2   The human casualties have been alarming, not only among the two warring camps, but more tragically, among civilians. The government's decision to pursue the military option, however, defies logic and is shortsighted. The use of military force should never be an option in the first place. It is not only ineffectives and costly in term of human lives. But, as the lessons of East Timor should have taught us by now it could be the one single major factor that pushes Aceh out of the republic. The nation's best hope in winning the hearts and minds of the Aceh people remains in the search for a negotiated settlement. The government has also started to implement a new law that gives Aceh sweeping autonomy and a greater share of revenue from natural resources. All good will and confidence-building could be wiped out overnight if the government decides to use the military option. - The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2  AFTER (THE SIGNING OF THE) LOI The new Letter of Intent (LoI) was finally signed after being delayed for almost a year. The signing brings hope for a better \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which has worsened in the past four years. Although the rupiah's exchange rate has gotten worse since the signing of the LoI, at least market trust has been tough enough to get along with the government in improving the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . Producing concrete policies is not easy. There are too many factors that should be considered. The most urgent one is the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . The signing of the LoI does not mean that the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  problem has been solved, but it is the start of hard work for the new government. The previous administration has failed to implement the LoI which had been signed. Thus, the current \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  team must abide by all the agreed points. We will just wait and see how the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  team will implement the agreement. This is the test so that we could assess whether the current team is a dream team or just a trivial team. - Republika \par \par \uc2  WHAT SHOULD BE DONE WITH ILLEGAL IMMIGRANTS AND REFUGEES? We were saddened by the ridiculous decision of about 434 illegal immigrants, most of whom were from Afghanistan. They preferred committing suicide by jumping to the rough sea to returning to Indonesia. They wanted to enter Australia as the country of their destination. They claimed to be asylum seekers as revealed by Rinnan, the captain of the Norwegian cargo ship who saved the illegal Afghan immigrants from a sinking Indonesian boat in international waters. The Australian government has refused to give entry to the illegal immigrants. The reason is certainly linked to the immigrants' presence at the Norwegian cargo ship, the country of their destination (Australia) and Indonesia's rejection of the illegal immigrants. Immigrants and refugees have the same connotation. The difference lies in our perception of them. The first may have to do with the process of their entry, while the second is attributed to the process of their fleeing from a conflict-stricken area. However, their reason for going to another country is the same - to get a better life in terms of security and social welfare. In a globalized world, immigration and seeking refuge have become a contemporary social problem. Maybe illegal immigrants and refugees are seeking political asylum. Perhaps they wish to avoid a confrontation with those in power in their country due to differences in political beliefs or to escape from becoming political victims. It is certainly complicated, when illegal immigrants or refugees refuse to live in a certain country as what we glean from the illegal immigrants refusal to return to Indonesia. Whoever they are, immigrants or refugees have the right to live on this earth and to be treated as human beings. Thus, it is time for the United Nations to deal with refugees fleeing political conflicts, but also with illegal immigrants flocking to certain countries. - Kompas. \par \par \uc2 Document antara0020010901dx8t00001\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  Growth of loss insurance industry predicted to drop 10%. \b0\par\par\uc2 329 \uc2 words\par \uc2 29 August 2001\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  The Indonesian Insurance Broke