\par\par \b \uc2  IMF APPROVES US$ 395 MILLION LOAN FOR INDONESIA. \b0\par\par\uc2 480 \uc2 words\par \uc2 10 September 2001\par \uc2 ANTARA - The Indonesian National News Agency\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 Asia Pulse Pte Limited. Asia Pulse gives no warranty or guarantee as to the accuracy of the information, Asia Pulse shall not be liable for errors or omissions in, or delays or interruptions to or cessation of delivery of, the data through its negligence or otherwise.\par \par \uc2  Washington DC, Sept 10 (ANTARA) - The executive board of the International Monetary Fund (IMF) completed on Monday its third review of Indonesia's performance under a three-year lending program and approved a US$ 395 million loan for the country. \par \par \uc2  The new disbursement is part of a total of US$ 5 billion in loans pledged by the IMF to help bail Indonesia out of its crippling \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis. \par \par \uc2  The IMF's first deputy managing director, Anne Krueger, after the meeting said the conclusion of the third review under the extended arrangement between Indonesia and the IMF was based on the adoption of early confidence-building measures, and the commitment of the new \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  team to maintain macroeconomic stability and reinvigorate reforms. \par \par \uc2  According to her, a significant improvement in market sentiments has already been achieved, and Indonesia has the potential to sustain a strong recovery of investment and output based on the firm and consistent implementation of the government's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  program. \par \par \uc2  "Indonesia's program aims to strengthen confidence by maintaining low inflation and sound \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  finances, while promoting the recovery of investment and output through accelerated asset recovery and structural reforms. The agreement on measures to keep the 2001 \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  on course, including through safeguards to minimize the risks represented by \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  decentralization, is an important signal of the government's commitment to macroeconomic stability," she said. \par \par \uc2  The planned non-inflationary financing of the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  will require accelerated enterprise privatization and IBRA (the Indonesian Bank Restructuring Agency) asset recovery, she said. \par \par \uc2  She welcomed the announcement of the main objectives of the 2002 \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , aimed at further \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  consolidation by strengthening the revenue base and better targeting of expenditures and transfers. \par \par \uc2  Krueger maintained that the replenishment of the government's guarantee fund for depositors will maintain confidence in Indonesia's banks, and the planned sale by IBRA of strategic stakes in banks BCA and Niaga will serve as an important litmus test of the government's commitment to reprivatizing the banking system. \par \par \uc2  She noted that measures to improve the governance of state banks and enhance bank supervision are also essential elements of the financial sector reform agenda. \par \par \uc2  Accelerating asset recovery and debt restructuring remains essential for reducing the debt burden, reviving investment flows, and securing the efficiency gains for sustaining growth, she said. \par \par \uc2  The Fund, she said, encourages IBRA to make renewed efforts to overcome recent delays and dispose of assets with improved governance and transparency. \par \par \uc2  "In this context, the Fund welcomes the government's commitment to make \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  the results of the Oversight Committee's independent reviews of IBRA's large restructurings, beginning with the first four reviews in August," she said. \par \par \uc2  Krueger asked the international community to provide strong support for the strengthened program made by the Indonesian government because Indonesian authorities have responded decisively to macroeconomic challenges and market \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2 Document antara0020010913dx9a000bb\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
