\par\par \b \uc2  RI continues to suffer lack of FDI - Survey. \b0\par\par\uc2 544 \uc2 words\par \uc2 19 September 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  12 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Foreign investors have continued to stay away from Indonesia despite an increase in the global flow of foreign direct investment (FDI) in 2000, according to the United Nation's World Investment Report 2001. \par \par \uc2  Explaining the report, economist Djisman Simanjuntak of the Centre for Strategic and International Studies (CSIS) said that the FDI figure in Indonesia last year was minus US$4.6 billion, meaning that foreign capital outflow exceeded foreign capital inflow by that amount, an increase from $2.7 billion in 1999. \par \par \uc2  "(The negative figure) was caused by foreign companies in Indonesia paying off their debts and one or two companies pulling out of the country," Djisman said in a media conference here. The annual report was published by the United Nations Conference on Trade and Development (UNCTAD). \par \par \uc2  The report also said that Indonesia's FDI index now ranked 134 out of 135 countries monitored by UNCTAD, or second from the bottom preceding Yemen, he said. \par \par \uc2  Djisman said that it was the third year in a row that the country had suffered negative foreign investment flow. \par \par \uc2  The flow of foreign direct investment dropped to minus $0.4 billion in 1998 after a peak of $4.7 billion in 1997, according to the report. \par \par \uc2  Djisman said that the mid-1997 \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis and the ensuing political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  had caused foreign investors to look elsewhere. \par \par \uc2  "Indonesia has yet to be seen as an attractive investment destination, mainly because of the lack of infrastructure and high quality skilled workers," he said. \par \par \uc2  Foreign investment through mergers and acquisitions (M&A) also dropped last year to $819 million compared to $1.2 billion in 1999. \par \par \uc2  Djisman said that pro-active initiatives from three government institutions involved with foreign direct investments - the Indonesian Bank Restructuring Agency (IBRA), the State Ministry for State Enterprises and the Investment Coordinating Board (BKPM) - were needed to attract reluctant investors. \par \par \uc2  So far, the sale of assets under IBRA and the privatization of state enterprises had not achieved much, he said, adding that an immediate divestment of 51 percent of Bank Central Asia (BCA) to a strategic investor could attract investors. \par \par \uc2  "It's a shame that we like to wait around," Djisman said. \par \par \uc2  According to the World Investment Report, the flow of foreign direct investment in Southeast Asia remains at pre-crisis levels. \par \par \uc2  FDI contribution from members of the Association of South East Asian Nations (ASEAN) toward developing countries in Asia continued to decline to only 10 percent in 2000 compared to more than 30 percent in the mid-1990s, it said. \par \par \uc2  "This was caused by the increase of investment in other countries in the region and Indonesia's divestment \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  since the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis," Djisman explained. \par \par \uc2  Global flows of foreign direct investment soared by 18 percent last year to a record $1.3 trillion, but was expected to decline this year, the report said. \par \par \uc2  "The main impetus behind both last year's growth and this year's projected drop are cross-border M&As, which constitute a substantial share of FDI worldwide," the report said. \par \par \uc2  However, after last year's peak the trend is now declining, affected by the overall slowdown in \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth, it said.(tnt) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010919dx9j0000g\par }\page {\par\fs20\b  \highlight22\uc2 Central bank \highlight\uc2  has yet to discount interest rate. \b0\par\par\uc2 453 \uc2 words\par \uc2 20 September 2001\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  has yet to decrease interest rate in view of monetary magnitude target such as inflation, following some world central banks step to cut the interest rate. \par \par \uc2  Director of BI Monetary Management Directorate Aslim Tajudin announced \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  has to take into account a number of matters before performing some discount to interest rate. \par \par \uc2  "International banks have imposed some discount to their interest rate in the wake of terror attack in the US, aiming at being alert to possibility of global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recession, especially in the US. The Fed alone has 7 times decrease its interest rate through 2001,"he said to press in Jakarta yesterday. \par \par \uc2  In Indonesia, Aslim continued, actually interest rate little by little has decreased. \par \par \uc2  "I think \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  interest rate decrease has been happening here. Though there exist some increase but it's getting less. We have to safeguard from inflation pressure," he asserted. \par \par \uc2  While auction result of this week shows \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  one-month future interest rate amounting to 17.66%, being unchanged compared to last week position. The auction itself managed to accumulate fund worth Rp11.8 trillion or 52.32% from amount of the auction received by \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Rupiah weakening \par \par \uc2  While rupiah yesterday was closed weaker against US$ by Rp90 (0.93%) to Rp9.610 following penetration of rupiah psychological threshold in result of huge buying in the absence of appropriate amount of supply. \par \par \uc2  Director of Bank Buana Indonesia Pardi Kendy informed the emergence of US$ demand has brought pressure to rupiah. \par \par \uc2  "Moreover through this week, rupiah has sharply penetrated psychological line having been remained for some time. Therefore market players basically not in need of US$ follow buying out US$ that makes rupiah more pushed down," he explained to Bisnis. \par \par \uc2  Telerate data shows rupiah was closed weaker at Rp9,610 per US$ at Jakarta market, weakening compared to Rp9,520 of Tuesday position. \par \par \uc2  Range of US$ trading is between Rp9,300 and Rp9,755. At international market (at 20.15), rupiah was sold at stronger position of Rp9,600 per US$. Adding that there also emerged in the market rumors pushing down rupiah. \par \par \uc2  "Among US$ genuine demand market players are blowing that Paris Club II is becoming \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2 , even to be annulled. Also news that market being wary over plan to impose \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  upon deposit by government. Such rumors will only give pressure to rupiah", he elaborated.. \par \par \uc2  Pardi added that weakening of rupiah is also in consequence to the lacking of supply from \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  or other party. "No party selling US$ has made rupiah penetrate easily. New psychological line before reaching Rp10,000 per US$ is Rp 9, 800 this week," he asserted. (yn). \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020010921dx9k00001\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
