\par\par \b \uc2  BI vows to do its utmost to defend rupiah. \b0\par\par\uc2 695 \uc2 words\par \uc2 20 September 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  will do everything in its power to prop up the rupiah and prevent it from sliding even further, Governor of \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  Sjahril Sabirin announced on Wednesday. \par \par \uc2  "\b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  is ready to intervene in the local unit if necessary," he told reporters. \par \par \uc2  There had been rumors later in the day that the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  had stepped in by selling around US$20 million. \par \par \uc2  Sjahril also said that \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  would not follow the U.S. Federal Reserve, which had cut \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  by 50 basis points earlier this week. \par \par \uc2  On Wednesday's weekly auction, the benchmark interest rate of \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's one-month SBI promissory notes was unchanged at 17.66 percent. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah has been under pressure over the past three days, which analysts said was due to a combination of high corporate dollar demand to repay debt and the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  created by last week's terrorist attacks on the U.S. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah ended lower at Rp 9.615 per U.S. dollar late on Wednesday compared to Rp 9,540 on Tuesday. \par \par \uc2  The local currency soared to as high as Rp 8,200 as confidence in the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  improved following the appointment of President Megawati Soekarnoputri late in July and the formation of a credible Cabinet team. \par \par \uc2  The government has targeted an average exchange rate of Rp 9,600 for this year, which means that the currency must stabilize at around Rp 8,400 throughout the remaining period of the year as it had been hovering below Rp 10,000 for quite some time. \par \par \uc2  Analysts, however, feared that the currency could drop to below the Rp 10,000 level again amid concerns that U.S. retaliation might trigger a new round of political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the country, which has the world's largest Muslim population. \par \par \uc2  The U.S. government has singled out Saudi Arabia-born millionaire Osama bin Laden as the prime suspect in the attacks. Bin Laden is believed to have stayed in Afghanistan as a guest of the Taliban government. \par \par \uc2  Some say that Megawati's visit to the U.S. this week could trigger unrest at home particularly if the U.S. government did attack Afghanistan. \par \par \uc2  Separately, \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  deputy governor Miranda Goeltom said that the weakening of the rupiah was partly due to the postponement of the Paris Club talks. \par \par \uc2  "The market sentiment is negative because the IMF and the Paris Club were forced to postpone their meetings due to the New York terrorist incident," Miranda said. \par \par \uc2  The International Monetary Fund (IMF) and the World Bank are postponing their annual meetings slated for Sept. 29 and Sept. 30 because of security concerns following the attacks against the U.S. It is not yet certain when the meetings will be resumed. \par \par \uc2  The Paris Club of creditor nations was expected to meet with the government last week to discuss the rescheduling of Indonesia's sovereign debts maturing in 2001 and 2002. The meeting was postponed because U.S. representatives were unable to travel to Paris following the terrorist attacks. \par \par \uc2  Miranda said that the negative sentiment was unfounded as the postponement of the meetings would not effect the club's decision on the rescheduling of Indonesia's sovereign debts. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, the Jakarta Stock Exchange (JSX) ended higher on Wednesday due to a rebound in a couple of blue chip stocks. \par \par \uc2  The JSX composite index ended up 2.1 percent or 8.617 points at 422.450 points. \par \par \uc2  Dealers said that sentiment had improved after the U.S. market fell only slightly on Tuesday. The Dow Jones Industrial Average closed down 17.30 points, or 0.2 percent at 8,903.40. \par \par \uc2  The U.S. stock market fell sharply when it resumed trading on Monday, after a four-day closure following the terrorist attacks. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, AP reported that U.S. stocks stabilized in early trading on Wednesday with tentative buying easing the selling pressure that depressed Wall Street in the aftermath of the terrorist attacks. \par \par \uc2  In the first hour of trading, the Dow Jones industrials rose 26.34 points to 8,930.04. (tnt) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010920dx9k0000p\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw139\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2085\pichgoal600
