\par\par \b \uc2  GOVT SHOULD SEEK DEBT RESCHEDULING UNTIL 2004 - ISEI CHAIRMAN. \b0\par\par\uc2 382 \uc2 words\par \uc2 20 September 2001\par \uc2 ANTARA - The Indonesian National News Agency\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 Asia Pulse Pte Limited. Asia Pulse gives no warranty or guarantee as to the accuracy of the information, Asia Pulse shall not be liable for errors or omissions in, or delays or interruptions to or cessation of delivery of, the data through its negligence or otherwise.\par \par \uc2  Jakarta, Sept 20 (ANTARA) - The government should seek the Paris Club forum's approval to reschedule Indonesia's debts over a period extending to 2004, the chairman of the Indonesian \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Scholars' Association (ISEI), Bambang Sudibyo, said here Thursday. \par \par \uc2      "The rescheduling should cover a period lasting until December \par \par \uc2  2004," Bambang said on the sidelines of a seminar on \b \highlight22\uc2 taxation\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2      In its draft of the 2002 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the government was to \par \par \uc2  propose the rescheduling of S$4.1 billion of debts to  the third \par \par \uc2  Paris Club forum. \par \par \uc2      According to Bambang, if the rescheduling program was applied to \par \par \uc2  the country's debt from 2002 to 2004, the amount involved could \par \par \uc2  reach more than US$7 billion. \par \par \uc2      "In the Paris Club forum, the government should ask for the \par \par \uc2  rescheduling of as much of the country's debts as possible," the \par \par \uc2  former finance minister said. \par \par \uc2      At the Consultative Group on Indonesia (CGI) forum, on the other \par \par \uc2  hand, the government should seek  smaller amounts of loans, he said. \par \par \uc2      The second Paris Club forum had agreed to reschedule  US$5.8 \par \par \uc2  billion of Indonesia's debts over  one-year period ending in March \par \par \uc2  2002. \par \par \uc2      About the rupiah's current depreciation, Bambang said, it was \par \par \uc2  mainly due to global factors, including the attack on World Trade \par \par \uc2  Center in New York last week. \par \par \uc2      There are pessimistic voices in the market on continuation of \par \par \uc2  foreign aid especially from the International Monetary Fund (IMF) and cancellation of the organization's annual meeting with the World Bank. \par \par \uc2  On President Megawati Soekarnoputri's current visit to the United States, Bambang said, the President might be put in a difficult position because of the U.S. accusations against Osama bin Laden as prime suspect of the terrorist attack. \par \par \uc2      "There would be \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  relations between the West and \par \par \uc2  predominantly Muslim  countries," he said. \par \par \uc2      Bambang mentioned as an example Pakistan where its government \par \par \uc2  supported the U.S moves while its people backed Afghanistan's ruling \par \par \uc2  Taliban. \par \par \uc2      "Such a condition will create \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," Bambang said. \par \par \uc2      The United States has warned Afghanistan it must surrender the \par \par \uc2  multimillionaire or face U.S. strikes. \par \par \uc2      However, Taliban gave clear signals that it was ready to face a \par \par \uc2  U.S. attacks rather than hand over Osama without clear evidence of his alleged guilt. \par \par \uc2 Document antara0020010922dx9k0000j\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw139\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2085\pichgoal600
