\par\par \b  \highlight22\uc2 BANK INDONESIA \highlight\uc2  OPTIMISTIC RUPIAH WILL STRENGHEN AGAIN. \b0\par\par\uc2 345 \uc2 words\par \uc2 20 September 2001\par \uc2 ANTARA - The Indonesian National News Agency\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 Asia Pulse Pte Limited. Asia Pulse gives no warranty or guarantee as to the accuracy of the information, Asia Pulse shall not be liable for errors or omissions in, or delays or interruptions to or cessation of delivery of, the data through its negligence or otherwise.\par \par \uc2  Jakarta, Sep 20 (ANTARA) - Governor of \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  Syahril Sabirin is optimistic that the rupiah will strengthen again following negotiations with the Paris Club of creditor nations. \par \par \uc2  "\b \highlight22\uc2 Central Bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  itself when the right time comes will intervene whenever necessary," Sabirin said after meeting with Vice President Hamzah Haz here on Thursday. \par \par \uc2  However, \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  will also lower the interest rate of \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's one-month promissory notes when the right time comes, as a high interest rate would only increase the burden of the bank. \par \par \uc2  The postponement of the Paris Club meeting originally scheduled on September 17, 2001, was the main cause of the weakening of the local unit. The postponement was merely a matter of time, not a serious problem, and the market was only exaggerting things, he said. \par \par \uc2  He also said that when the IMF signed the new LoI, many companies rushed for the dollar. "They may have their own reasons," he said. \par \par \uc2  He also said that he and the vice president also discussed why \par \par \uc2  the rupiah has weakened, although the IMF has signed the LoI. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah has been under pressure over the past three days, \par \par \uc2  which analysts said was due to a combination of high corporate demand for the dollar to repay debts and the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  created by last week's terrorist attacks on the US. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah ended at Rp 9.615 per US dolar late on Thursday \par \par \uc2  compared to Rp 9.615 on Wednesday. \par \par \uc2  The International Monetary Fund (IMF) and the World Bank are \par \par \uc2  postponing their annual meetings  slated for Sept 29 and Spet 30 \par \par \uc2  because of security concern following the terrorist attack. \par \par \uc2  The Paris Club of creditor nations was expected to meet with \par \par \uc2  the government last week to discuss the rescheduling of Indonesia's \par \par \uc2  sovereign debts maturing in 2001 and 2002. \par \par \uc2  The meeting was postponed because the US representatives were \par \par \uc2  unable to travel to Paris following the terrorist attacks. \par \par \uc2  Syahril said the vice president has instructed the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\par \par \uc2  authorities to do everything in their power to calm down the market. \par \par \uc2 Document antara0020010922dx9k000gs\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  IMF - RI should be more optimistic. \b0\par\par\uc2 461 \uc2 words\par \uc2 21 September 2001\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  The IMF has asked Indonesians to be optimistic over Paris Club II, with its chief in Indonesia, David Nellor, saying that while the world's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and political situation is rife with \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 , there is no reason to believe the Paris Club II meeting would fail. \par \par \uc2  "Creditors have responded positively, especially in view of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reforms in the letter of intent," he said here on the sidelines of a seminar yesterday. \par \par \uc2  He also pointed out that almost all members of Paris Club sit in the IMF board. \par \par \uc2  In Paris Club II in March 2000, Indonesia received a debt rescheduling of US$5.8 billion. \par \par \uc2  The IMF, said Nellor, would not change its stance on the government despite the US tragedy 'Black Tuesday'. \par \par \uc2  The situation now is different from that during April 2001, he added, when Paris Club should have met in a meeting that was postponed due to the delay in LoI. \par \par \uc2  The IMF, said Nellor, would continue to hold a review every three months in order to keep abreast of the general \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  situation. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, former finance minister Bambang Sudibyo said that the government could actually reschedule matured loan payment in Paris Club III amounting to US$7 billion if the group could reschedule foreign debts beyond that which would mature in 2002. \par \par \uc2  "It would be ideal if the rescheduling includes those that mature in December 2004, amounting to US$7 billion." \par \par \uc2  A member of the staff of the finance minister, Anggito Abimanyu, said Paris Club III would reschedule loan payment of $4.1 billion, which is the figure in the draft state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  RAPBN 2002. \par \par \uc2  "The strategy of the government is to seek the largest amount for rescheduling and the smallest in new loans in the CGI meeting", he said, "and to alleviate the government's foreign debt burden and the new state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 ." \par \par \uc2  "New loans from CGI should be less than US$4 billion." \par \par \uc2  Bambang said such a move would prove that the Megawati government is better than that of Abdurrahman Wahid's. \par \par \uc2  Bambang predicted that talks in Paris Club III and CGI would be tougher than in the past, due to the heated ties between the US and Muslim countries. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, Nellor hoped the government would come up with more \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  flexible policies but should not alter macro-\b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  policies as the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  remains \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Nellor predicted that the 11 September tragedy would adversely effect the US \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and Indonesia's exports and direct investment. \par \par \uc2  IMF plans to discuss these issues in the next meeting with the government. \par \par \uc2  Bambang Sudibyo also said that the US tragedy would lead to the postponement of Paris Club II, which was slated for 10 September, and the CGI meeting in November. (m04/01). \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020010921dx9l000gv\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
