\par\par \b  \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia \highlight\uc2  mulls lowering interest rate. \b0\par\par\uc2 701 \uc2 words\par \uc2 21 September 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  12 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  (BI) will allow its benchmark interest rate to decline if pressure on prices and the rupiah continue to lessen over the next couple of weeks, \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  deputy governor Miranda Goeltom said on Thursday. \par \par \uc2  Miranda said that although \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  would retain its tight money \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  for the moment it was possible that reign over the \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  would be considerably lessened in the near future. \par \par \uc2  "I think if deflation is retained this September and there is no longer any persistent pressure on the rupiah, then there is every possibility to relax the monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," she said on the sidelines of a hearing with the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  Commission IX for financial and development planning affairs. \par \par \uc2  Miranda said that the weakening of the rupiah over the past three days was only a "hiccup", and not a persistent threat to the exchange rate. \par \par \uc2  "Without any persistent pressure on the rupiah, of course the way toward a relaxed monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  will become more open," she added. \par \par \uc2  Miranda said that the bank's job was to keep the country from high inflation, which was also part of the deal with the International Monetary Fund (IMF). In the latest letter of intent, the government agreed to bring the 12-month inflation level to well within the 9 percent to 11 percent target range by the end of the year. \par \par \uc2  "But we also need to see if liquidity is a problem at this time, and we should treat that with care," she added. \par \par \uc2  Miranda said that the bank's \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  to absorb only 53 percent of the bids offered for \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's one-month SBI promissory notes at the weekly auction on Wednesday was an indication of the bank's greater faith in the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  because it gave it greater liquidity to maneuver. \par \par \uc2  "That's the hint, that means there is a potential to lower the interest rate in the weeks to come," she said. \par \par \uc2  Miranda stressed that the downturn in the rupiah to the U.S. dollar recently was only temporary and caused by speculators spinning off rumors that Osama bin Laden, the prime suspect of the U.S. attack last week, may have been hiding in the country. \par \par \uc2  There was no rational reason for the rupiah to weaken but that of the "911" attack in the United States last week, she said, referring to the attacks which came on Sept. 11. \par \par \uc2  "The market became a bit worried, followed by those widespread rumors, which, although unbelievable, could be used to provoke the market," Miranda said, adding that as the rumor eases, the rupiah should become more stable within the next few days. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah has been under pressure over the past three days, which analysts said was due to a combination of high corporate dollar demand to repay debts and the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  created by last week's terrorist attacks on the United States. \par \par \uc2  The local currency, which had enjoyed strong rates after Megawati Soekarnoputri's ascension to the presidency, had dropped to levels of Rp 9,500 this week. The rupiah had been hovering at Rp 11,000 prior to Megawati's presidency. \par \par \uc2  The dollar was quoted between Rp 9,425 and Rp 9,470 late Thursday, much lower than Rp 9,530 to Rp 9,590 late Wednesday. \par \par \uc2  The U.S. currency touched an intraday high of Rp 9,735 as local companies bought dollars to repay debts or to pay for imports. \par \par \uc2  Analysts said that the higher rupiah rate was caused by foreign players taking profits on the dollar's recent strength. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  had also reportedly sold about US$10 million through brokers to help the local currency. \par \par \uc2  However, analysts said that the rupiah was also facing pressure over a possible retaliation by the United States, which could incite further unrest in Indonesia as it has the world's largest Muslim population. \par \par \uc2  Miranda reiterated earlier statements that \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  would take steps to assure that the rupiah would not fall any further. \par \par \uc2  "We still have room to intervene, but of course I will not tell you whether we have or have not done so," she said.(tnt) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010920dx9l00061\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
