\par\par \b \uc2  IMF dismisses worries over Paris Club meeting delay. \b0\par\par\uc2 607 \uc2 words\par \uc2 21 September 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): The International Monetary Fund (IMF) dismissed on Thursday worries that a delay in the Paris Club meeting had put at risk a US$2.8 billion debt rescheduling deal for this year. \par \par \uc2  The IMF senior resident representative for Jakarta, David C.L. Nellor, expressed confidence that Indonesia's debt rescheduling deal with the Paris Club was safe. \par \par \uc2  "I am sure that major creditor countries, having expressed very positive comments on Indonesia's reforms program during the IMF board meeting on Sept. 10, will reflect those (comments) at the Paris Club," Nellor said on the sidelines of a seminar on \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  reforms. \par \par \uc2  The Paris Club meeting, slated for mid-September, was delayed indefinitely after its American delegation was unable to attend following the devastating terror attacks on the United States. \par \par \uc2  The meeting of the Paris Club should have formalized the rescheduling of Indonesia's $2.8 billion sovereign debt maturing in March 2002. \par \par \uc2  The delay came after Indonesia painstakingly secured an IMF lending agreement, without which the Paris Club deal was void. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  over the Paris Club meeting and concerns over the U.S. \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , Indonesia's biggest export market, are weighing heavy on the fragile rupiah. \par \par \uc2  Nellor agreed the Paris Club delay did cause \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 , but he said the members of the club were unlikely to change their stance on Indonesia. \par \par \uc2  He declined to estimate when the Paris Club would meet, saying the announcement should come from the club. \par \par \uc2  He also said he saw no immediate need to alter the IMF's position on Indonesia despite a looming global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recession. \par \par \uc2  The fund recently approved a $400 million loan package to Indonesia, after the government agreed to new \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reform targets under the Letter of Intent (LoI). \par \par \uc2  Nellor said any plans to revise Indonesia's reform program, would be discussed by the fund and the government during the quarterly review of the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  outlook. \par \par \uc2  "We need to reassess what's happening in the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and what's happening in Indonesia and make adjustments accordingly. Whether that involves changes in the \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , changes in the targets, we have to wait and see," he explained. \par \par \uc2  "It's not yet time to come to a strong judgment. At the moment people are making assessments of what the implications of the tragedy might be for U.S. \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth and global growth," he added. \par \par \uc2  Nellor further said the 2002 \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  assumptions were still relevant. \par \par \uc2  "The \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  presented to the legislature attempted to be fairly conservative, so that's a strong backdrop to this \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  situation," he said. \par \par \uc2  Nellor said Indonesia had adopted a sound \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reform program as contained in its LoI. "I think the investment community in general has recognized this," he said. \par \par \uc2  Nellor added that President Megawati Soekarnoputri's visit to Washington was also an opportunity to highlight Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reforms progress before foreign investors. \par \par \uc2  Separately, former finance minister Bambang Sudibyo said the government should seek a debt rescheduling deal that would last until 2004. \par \par \uc2  By then, he said Indonesia would have finalized consolidating its \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  to eliminate the containing \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Earlier, the government said it would seek a third Paris Club debt rescheduling deal to ease pressure on the 2002 \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  from foreign debt payments. \par \par \uc2  For the same reason, it also indicated that it would seek more loans from creditor countries under the Consultative Group on Indonesia (CGI), which will meet in November to discuss new loans for Indonesia. \par \par \uc2  But Bambang said the government should address this concern more by rescheduling its debts rather than accumulating new ones. (bkm) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010920dx9l00063\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
