\par\par \b \uc2  Single digit inflation rate still possible - BPS. \b0\par\par\uc2 622 \uc2 words\par \uc2 25 September 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  12 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Although year-on-year inflation has been running at double digit rates since March, ending the year with an inflation rate of below 10 percent was still possible on the back of lower inflation expected for September and October, the Central Bureau of Statistics (BPS) said. \par \par \uc2  The BPS said on Monday that the consumer price index for September and October should be lower so as to produce single digit inflation by the year's end. \par \par \uc2  By guaranteeing the supply of goods and services, the government could slow down the inflation rate during these two months, BPS chief Sudarti Surbakti said. \par \par \uc2  "The chances are slim, but reaching single digit inflation is still possible," she said during a hearing with the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2 ' Commission IX for financial affairs. \par \par \uc2  The government has targeted an inflation rate of 9.3 percent for this year. \par \par \uc2  Hopes for single digit inflation hinged on the September and October rates, as seasonal factors would drive inflation up in November and December, Sudarti said. \par \par \uc2  In August, the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  saw a drop in inflation of 0.21 percent, the first such drop since September last year. \par \par \uc2  Sudarti said a similar fall in inflation in September was unlikely. \par \par \uc2  She cited a weakening rupiah and the lingering impact of higher electricity charges as being behind inflationary pressure this month. \par \par \uc2  Although the rupiah had strengthened since the new government took office in late July, the pressure of foreign debt repayments is weighing heavily on the local unit. \par \par \uc2  On Indonesia's Gross Domestic Product (GDP) growth, BPS deputy chief Kusmadi Saleh said a rate of 3.5 percent for this year was reasonable, despite concerns of a slowing export market in the U.S. \par \par \uc2  The U.S. \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  is edging closer to recession after the recent terrorist attacks on New York and Washington. \par \par \uc2  The United States remains for Indonesia, as for most other countries, the largest single export market. \par \par \uc2  A further plunge in the U.S. market could send the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  spiraling into recession, thus hampering Indonesia's export growth. \par \par \uc2  But Kusmadi Saleh said that with first semester GDP growth of 3.37 percent, he was confident Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  could make it to 3.5 percent. \par \par \uc2  About 60 percent of the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  is driven by small and midsize industries, according to Kusmadi. \par \par \uc2  Since the 1997 \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis, small and midsize industries have assumed a greater role in the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , he explained. \par \par \uc2  "Growth in this sector (small and midsize industries) reached between 3 percent and 4 percent compared to last year," he said. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, the government has estimated that the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the second semester of this year will book a lower \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  of US$2.71 billion as against $5.07 billion in the first semester. \par \par \uc2  State Minister for National Development Kwik Kian Gie said the lower \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  would be the result of a surplus of foreign aid over the outflow of foreign debt repayments. \par \par \uc2  For the second half of this year, the government has estimated an inflow of $2.81 billion in aid against an outflow of $1.45 billion in debt principle payments. \par \par \uc2  Also, Indonesia's improved political situation would mitigate the outflow of private capital, he added. \par \par \uc2  Kwik estimated a lower capital outflow of $4.07 billion compared to $4.98 billion during the first semester. \par \par \uc2  He further said it was too early to say whether the terrorist attack on the U.S. would send the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  into recession, and thus hamper new investment inflows. \par \par \uc2  "There are too many \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 . People are not sure where the world \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  is heading," he told reporters after a hearing with the House \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  commission.(bkm) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010925dx9p0000h\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw139\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2085\pichgoal600
