\par\par \b \uc2  IMF says LoI to remain as is. \b0\par\par\uc2 518 \uc2 words\par \uc2 6 October 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  20 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  Berni K Moestafa, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \par \uc2  Following its positive remarks about Indonesia's 2001 \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  performance, the International Monetary Fund (IMF) has also expressed confidence in the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reform targets, despite a looming global recession. \par \par \uc2  Daniel Citrin, leading a visiting IMF team to Indonesia, said on Friday that Indonesia would not need to revise its reform targets. \par \par \uc2  "There is no need to change the targets," said Citrin in response to questions about the Letter of Intent (LoI), a lending agreement with the IMF that outlines Indonesia's reform targets. \par \par \uc2  Citrin gave no further details. But his assurance could soothe growing concerns here over the fallout from last month's terrorist attacks against the U.S. \par \par \uc2  The attacks crippled U.S. consumer confidence, and are expected to drag down investment confidence as well, a combination that could leave the world's largest \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  mired in a prolonged slump. \par \par \uc2  Indonesia, which has exported its way out of the 1997 \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis, mainly to a previously bullish U.S market, may soon find itself losing steam as it tries to sustain its nascent \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery. \par \par \uc2  Export and strong consumer \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  have been fueling Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth. Now, exporters are warning that sales may drop by 20 percent from last year's US$62 billion. \par \par \uc2  This outlook could undermine consumer confidence, as consumers are likely to delay \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  amid the heightened \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Calls by businessmen for an \b \highlight22\uc2 economic stimulus\b0 \highlight\uc2  package received only a lukewarm, if not cold, response from the government. \par \par \uc2  The government dashed hopes for a cash-based emergency package, saying that it was not always what the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  needed. \par \par \uc2  Finance Minister Boediono said the best \b \highlight22\uc2 stimulus\b0 \highlight\uc2  Indonesia could hope for was political and security stability. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  on the global front, and the government's apparent indecision in the face of it, has taken its toll on the rupiah. \par \par \uc2  Since the Sept. 11 attack the rupiah has lost 7 percent of its value, and only recently regained some ground. \par \par \uc2  Bank of Indonesia Deputy Governor, Miranda Goeltom, said the market's aversion to the local unit was fading. \par \par \uc2  She said the market had begun to judge outside developments from a more rational perspective. This, coupled with the Bank of Indonesia's intervention, had been responsible for the recent strengthening of the rupiah, she said. \par \par \uc2  "The market has overreacted on worries of a U.S. strike," Miranda explained, referring to a possible attack against Afghanistan for refusing to surrender Osama bin Laden. \par \par \uc2  Miranda said the slump in the rupiah was only temporary and expressed confidence that the unit would regain its stability. \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  has kept \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  tight to weaken dollar buyers by absorbing the rupiah into promissory notes. \par \par \uc2  Rates on Bank of Indonesia promissory notes have been hovering well above the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  assumed level of 15 percent. They now stand at 17.59 percent. \par \par \uc2  And despite signs of a stronger rupiah, Miranda indicated \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  were to remain high. \par \par \uc2  "We will refer to achieving our base money supply target this year," she said. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020011008dxa6000bo\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
