\par\par \b \uc2  Possibility of U.S. attack taunts rupiah's gains - Experts. \b0\par\par\uc2 526 \uc2 words\par \uc2 8 October 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  20 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  Berni K Moestafa, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \par \uc2  The probable U.S. strike against Afghanistan could block the rupiah's timid upward trend this week, as the market geared for a long dollar position to anticipate a backlash from radical groups here, analysts said. \par \par \uc2  Head of the debt income section at PT Vickers Ballas Indonesia, Wiwan Wiradjaja said market players remained wary over the domestic reaction to an anticipated U.S.-led military strike against Afghanistan. \par \par \uc2  "The rupiah is recovering, but will likely slip on unexpected bad news," Wiwan told The Jakarta Post over the weekend. \par \par \uc2  He said most players had factored in the possible U.S. strike, but were still unsure on how that could affect domestic security. \par \par \uc2  "If calls for a holy war (by Muslim militants) intensify after the attack, this will have a downward impact on the rupiah," he predicted. \par \par \uc2  Local radical groups have been staging anti-U.S protests over the past few weeks in response to America's planned attack against Afghanistan. \par \par \uc2  A military strike seems inevitable, as Afghanistan's Taliban regime continues to defy demands from the West to hand over Osama Bin Laden, the prime suspect behind last month's terrorist attack in the U.S. \par \par \uc2  The disaster, crushing U.S consumer and business confidence, has also left a gaping hole in the world \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Reflecting this grim outlook, the rupiah has been steadily losing ground, amounting to seven percent in value since the attack. \par \par \uc2  Currency dealers have said the rupiah's past rebound after breaching the 10,000 barrier against the U.S dollar last week, was in part due to players cooling off from the panic that followed the terrorist attack. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  stepped in with intervention, and has said it would continue to do so if necessary. \par \par \uc2  "Trading has been relatively thin; this should help \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  intervention moves," Wiwan continued. \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  has also been keeping a tight lid on \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  to absorb liquidity and ease inflationary pressure. \par \par \uc2  But stock analysts warned of fresh rupiah supplies flooding the money market by investors dumping shares in favor of dollars. \par \par \uc2  Dropping export revenues subsequent to the slump in the U.S. market, also threatened the inflow of dollar supplies. \par \par \uc2  "Fundamentally, the rupiah is undervalued, however, given the still negative outlook, it's unlikely it will strengthen any time soon," Wiwan explained. \par \par \uc2  According to Wiwan, the rupiah could hover this week between 9,700 to 9,900. Last week, it ended trading down at 9,800 from 9,710 a week before. \par \par \uc2  A dealer at a local securities company said regional security \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 , and the absence of fresh leads at home, could prolong the market index fall to its fifth week. \par \par \uc2  According to her, players bow to selling pressure by the few foreign ones dumping shares in the wake of increased radical movements. \par \par \uc2  "At this moment, investors prefer not to hold stocks," she said. \par \par \uc2  She predicted the Jakarta Stock Exchange Composite Index may still test the 350 level, after ending last week down at 381.59 from 392.47 a week earlier. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020011008dxa80000b\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\p