\par\par \b \uc2  Batam to receive free trade status by year end - Official. \b0\par\par\uc2 603 \uc2 words\par \uc2 8 October 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  24 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  Tantri Yuliandini, The Jakarta Post, Batam, Riau \par \par \uc2  The government is expected to grant Batam Island in the Riau province the long anticipated Free Trade Zone (FTZ) status by the end of the year, the Batam Industrial Development Authority chairman Ismeth Abdullah said. \par \par \uc2  He said that the government was currently deliberating the new bill on the status of Batam and that it was "serious" and had the backing of the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "All it needs (for the status to be imposed) is for it to be formalized. There was a dispute before about the FTZ status, but it has been resolved," Ismeth told visiting foreign reporters. \par \par \uc2  He said that the FTZ status was important to Batam and its future as Indonesia's center of industry, as it would act as a magnet to attract foreign investors into the country. \par \par \uc2  A Free Trade Zone status would enable companies on Batam to import goods without paying customs duties and \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2 , pending their eventual processing, transshipment, or reexportation. \par \par \uc2  Batam, located some 20 kilometers from Singapore, was initially declared as an industrial bonded zone in 1978 to attract foreign investment and bolster export competitiveness. The same status was later given to the nearby islands of Rempang and Galang, making the zone a total area of 715 square kilometers. \par \par \uc2  However, Ismeth said, the island had technically acted as a free trade zone beginning 10 to 15 years ago and \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  incentives originally intended for industry had also been enjoyed by all residents of Batam, including Indonesian companies even when their products and services were not destined for export. \par \par \uc2  This \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  led to resentment among companies based outside the island, leading the government to reimpose value added \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  (VAT) in 1998 to ensure equitable \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  treatment. \par \par \uc2  The ruling, which was originally to take effect in April last year, met with strong resistance both from Batam residents and foreign industrialists based here. \par \par \uc2  It was then decided to postpone the imposition until next year. \par \par \uc2  Since then the status of the island has been in question, not only due to \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  over \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  incentives but also because legally a bonded zone status would not include noncommercial inhabitants. \par \par \uc2  Ismeth said that the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  had caused many foreign investors to postpone their investments on the island and from the expected 100 new investors last year only 49 had pushed through with their planned investment. \par \par \uc2  Foreign direct investment (FDI) on Batam has steadily increased even during the years of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis. Last year FDI was US$2.8 billion compared to $2.3 billion the year before. \par \par \uc2  Ismeth said that between January and September this year approvals for foreign direct investment totaled $382.1 million comprising 55 new investments and 16 expansions. \par \par \uc2  He said that he expected some 80 new foreign direct investments to arrive by the end of the year. \par \par \uc2  However, the effects of the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  slowdown in the aftermath of the U.S. terrorist attacks would also effect business activities on the island. \par \par \uc2  "The New York tragedy makes us worry because who knows how it will tighten investment worldwide," Ismeth said, adding that due to the recession Japanese electronics company Hitachi had pulled out of the island. \par \par \uc2  Exports from Batam would also likely drop between 10 to 12 percent this year compared to $6.8 billion last year, he said. \par \par \uc2  "In general (the recession) will affect us, but we hope we will not be hit hard," Ismeth said, explaining that he expects new projects to commence early next year that would compensate for this year's decline. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020011008dxa80000c\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
