\par\par \b \uc2  Govt told to safeguard domestic  \highlight22\uc2 economy \highlight\uc2 . \b0\par\par\uc2 676 \uc2 words\par \uc2 8 October 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  Berni K. Moestafa, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \par \uc2  Experts have urged the government to ensure legal certainty and restore security in order to attract new investment to help cushion the country from the looming global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  slump. \par \par \uc2  Former finance minister Bambang Sudibyo said that the administration of President Megawati Soekarnoputri must give a signal to the market that it was serious in resolving the present legal imbroglio and ongoing security problems. \par \par \uc2  "The key is to attract new investment, but we need legal certainty and security guarantees. This is what has been lacking," Bambang told The Jakarta Post on Sunday. \par \par \uc2  He explained that there was strong evidence now that the world \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  was heading toward a recession, but there was nothing the government could do to prevent it from happening except to moderate the impact on the country by taking concerted measures to prop up domestic investment. \par \par \uc2  Centre for Strategic and International Studies (CSIS) economist Hadi Soesastro concurred. \par \par \uc2  Hadi said that the government must resolve "the domestic mess", including security and legal problems, to entice new investment so as to help the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  to grow and create more jobs. \par \par \uc2  "An \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  package alone will not be sufficient," he said. \par \par \uc2  Some businessmen had earlier called on the government to provide an \b \highlight22\uc2 economic stimulus\b0 \highlight\uc2  package, as have been prepared by other governments in the region, to help the country brace itself for the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  repercussions of last month's terrorist attacks in the U.S. \par \par \uc2  The attacks have left the world teetering on the brink of a recession, pushed by a sharp plunge in U.S. consumer and business confidence. \par \par \uc2  Economist Umar Juoro of the Association of Indonesian Muslim Intellectuals (ICMI) predicted the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  slowdown would extend well into next year. \par \par \uc2  "It's going to be tough without a \b \highlight22\uc2 stimulus\b0 \highlight\uc2  package from the government," he told the Post over the weekend. \par \par \uc2  But Umar said Indonesia could hardly afford a \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  binge to spur \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth given its gaping \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Instead, he suggested redirecting bank credit portfolios away from \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  promissory notes to the productive sector. \par \par \uc2  Since the 1997 financial crisis crippled the country's banking sector, many banks have come to rely on government bonds and \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  certificates, known as SBIs, for their earnings. \par \par \uc2  This situation places huge \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  constraints on the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , as the government must pay interest on the bonds. \par \par \uc2  Umar said that if the banks were to skim off 10 percent of their bond interest earnings and allocate it to fresh lending, then \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth should be stimulated. \par \par \uc2  "It's \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  money, and most banks are now state-owned anyway," he said. \par \par \uc2  Banking analyst Mirza Adityaswara at PT Indosuez W.I. Carr Securities said \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  should ease its monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "A one percent cut in SBI rates amounts to a saving of Rp 2.5 trillion, which the government can spend on development," he said. \par \par \uc2  Thus far, \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  has persisted in keeping rates high in order to lower the base money supply to Rp 110 trillion. \par \par \uc2  Meeting that target is one of the promises the government has made to the International Monetary Fund (IMF). \par \par \uc2  Mirza said the government should persuade the IMF to ease its base money target to allow the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  to lower SBI rates. \par \par \uc2  Senior economist Raden Pardede at PT Danareksa Securities concurred, but cited security, political and legal certainty as preconditions. \par \par \uc2  "\b \highlight22\uc2 Uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  makes people run for cash which raises the base money supply, hence we have high SBI rates," he said. \par \par \uc2  Raden said a \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal stimulus\b0 \highlight\uc2  under this and next years' tight budgets was unlikely unless the government aimed for higher revenue targets. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  collection, privatization, asset sales, and raising new foreign loans were among the best options for achieving that goal. \par \par \uc2  But he warned that the rising nationalism of legislators would likely hamper the achievement of privatization and asset sales targets. \par \par \uc2  "If we want a \b \highlight22\uc2 stimulus\b0 \highlight\uc2  there is a price to pay, like paying interest on new loans or losing ownership of assets," he said. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020011008dxa80000e\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  Mega's  \highlight22\uc2 economic \highlight\uc2  team gets criticisms. \b0\par\par\uc2 475 \uc2 words\par \uc2 8 October 2001\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  The government's moves to stimulate the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and in facing global \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  is seen as 'minimalist', as its pro-market and pro-foreigners stance seem not to have boosted the rupiah, economists say. \par \par \uc2  Cides economist Umar Juoro said the government is not skillful enough to lift the nation out of the crisis. \par \par \uc2  "We should not wait for the situation to become calm. Even a big country as the US was swift to respond," he told Bisnis yesterday. \par \par \uc2  The government, said Juoro, tends to be minimalist. \par \par \uc2  He cited Finance Minister Boediono's statement that the government puts importance on the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  as the bottom line. \par \par \uc2  In fact, he added, the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  is merely an intermediate target. \par \par \uc2  "What's important is how to move the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , growth and employment." \par \par \uc2  Juoro also said the targets in the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  APBN 2001 are difficult to realize as there are many constraints, including debt repayment. \par \par \uc2  He urged the government to channel credits for small and medium businesses amounting to 10% of funds allocated for government bonds. \par \par \uc2  "Interest on bonds are paid by the people, and as such the funds should be returned to the people," he said. \par \par \uc2  He said the APBN 2001 allocates fresh funds of Rp60 trillion to pay interest on bonds in order to prevent banks from going bankrupt. \par \par \uc2  Chairman of the Indonesian chamber of commerce and industry (Kadin) Aburizal Bakrie earlier said many have become disappointed with the government, especially on job opportunities. \par \par \uc2  Separately, Econit Advisory Group economist Hendri Saparini questioned the reason behind the fall of the rupiah despite the government's pro-market and pro-foreigners stance. \par \par \uc2  He noted that market optimism was formed the moment Megawati replaced Abdurrahman Wahid as president, creating a new political hope. \par \par \uc2  "The fall of the rupiah indicates something clear... \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  blessing on the government was a momentum that had not been capitalized well to recover the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," he told Bisnis last week. \par \par \uc2  He added that the rupiah fell precisely as other currencies strengthened against the US$ in the wake of the 11 September attack. \par \par \uc2  In fact, on Tuesday the rupiah went beyond 10.000 per US$. "Without the intervention of \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  it would have been hard to defend the rupiah." \par \par \uc2  Hendri pointed at poor exports and matured debts as the reasons behind the rupiah's fall. \par \par \uc2  "The APBN 2002 is very pro-creditor. Payment for principal and interests amount to Rp129 trillion or 39% of all \b \highlight22\uc2 expenditure\b0 \highlight\uc2 . The figures do not make sense." \par \par \uc2  Boediono last week said the weak rupiah is a temporary matter, and that it would strengthen once the security situation improves. He and the governor of the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  disagreed with planning minister Kwik Kian Gie, who promoted emergency steps such as applying a fixed rate system that Kwik says could stabilize the situation. (m04/ab). \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020011008dxa8000gq\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  Govt urged to take emergency measures. \b0\par\par\uc2 381 \uc2 words\par \uc2 9 October 2001\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  Indonesian Chamber of Commerce and Industry (Kadin) urge government to immediately take emergency measures to anticipate the impact of world \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recession upon the national \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Chairman of Kadin Aburizal Bakrie predicted of a potent slump of up to 30% in Indonesia's export following WTC tragedy and US attacks to Afghanistan. \par \par \uc2  Global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  downturn resulting from the two tragedic events would definitely hurt Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  both in its international trade and national \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the coming years. \par \par \uc2  "The present \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  condition in world and national \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  requires special attention from the government. Therefore we urge government to take emergency measures against such a difficult situation," he said here yesterday in the sidelines of ministerial meeting discussing Indonesia's position in the coming WTO meeting. \par \par \uc2  According to him WTC tragedy and US' reprisal attacks against Afghanistan will bring the world \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  into a deep recession, of which will greatly affected national \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  He further warned of the probable shut down in operations of companies and a massive lay offs if no emergency measures were immediately taken to save the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  from falling down. \par \par \uc2  He demanded government to launch a change in export \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  line and to intensify focus on optimalisation of domestic market including adding volume of money in response to the worsening \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  condition. \par \par \uc2  Kadin also proposed for a \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  change in credit extension for business expansion through soft loan, \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  reduction, and interest rate lowering. \par \par \uc2  New Package \par \par \uc2  Minister of Trade and Industry Rini MS Soewandi cited a need for a new package of \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , primarily those related to export, to overcome the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  problems as US reprisal attacks to Afghanistan is estimated to worsen the country's export performance. \par \par \uc2  "With the potent global recession resulting from the WTC tragedy, our export will likely to suffer from a significant slump," she said. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile real sector association sees the attack will bring real sector business into a more \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  condition. \par \par \uc2  Chairman of steel cutting association Jimmie Soelaiman even said such a condition will put businessmen into a confusion for not knowing what to do since demand in domestic market is decreasing. \par \par \uc2  "The already small domestic absorption will likely to decrease due to the difficult condition," he said.(05/cp/ib). \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020011009dxa900002\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  Government should take emergency measures - kadin. \b0\par\par\uc2 437 \uc2 words\par \uc2 9 October 2001\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  Indonesian Chamber of Commerce and Industry (KADIN) urges government to immediately take action of emergency in a bid to anticipate excess of world \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recession to domestic \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Aburizal 'Ical' Bakrie, chairperson of KADIN expected effects of infrastructure destruction at WTC and US retaliation attack to Afghanistan would potentially cut down 30% of whole Indonesian export. \par 