ister of Industry and Trading MS Soewandi at the same place contended the need of new \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  package to cope with \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  problem especially regarding export following the more warming of world security condition. \par \par \uc2  According to her, impacts of US attack to Afghanistan would aggravate Indonesian export position. Thus, there need to be new \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  to overcome the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  problem especially in terms of export. \par \par \uc2  "With global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  slowdown threat following WTC catastrophe recently, our \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  must be shaking," Rini said. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile Real Sector Association perceives US Attack to Afghanistan resulting in rupiah rate against US$ to penetrate Rp10,000 has brought more \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  to domestic real sector business. \par \par \uc2  Even, according to Jimmie Soelaiman, Chairperson of All Indonesia Steel Sheet Cutting Association, the condition has made businessmen became confused and desperate as domestic demand also decreased. \par \par \uc2  "Domestic absorption power has been decreasing in consequence to the condition," he noted. (05/cp/ib). \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020011009dxa9000b7\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
