\par\par \b \uc2  Projections for 2002  \highlight22\uc2 budget \highlight\uc2  revised down. \b0\par\par\uc2 382 \uc2 words\par \uc2 10 October 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  Berni K. Moestafa, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  approved on Tuesday government-proposed revised assumptions for the 2002 draft state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  in a move to take account of the heightened \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  surrounding the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  next year. \par \par \uc2  The government has revised downward almost all key assumptions in the 2002 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  draft which was submitted to legislators last month. \par \par \uc2  Under the new assumptions, gross domestic product (GDP) growth has been lowered to four percent from five percent previously. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah's exchange rate against the U.S. dollar has been lowered to 9,000 from 8,500, while forecast inflation has been upped to nine percent from eight percent. \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  interest rate is maintained at 14 percent, while the original assumed crude oil price of US$22 per barrel has also been maintained. \par \par \uc2  At the same time, the oil production target has been raised to 1.32 million barrels per day (bpd) from 1.23 million bpd. \par \par \uc2  The revisions followed a two-day meeting with the House \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  commission, and come as the government braces for a full-fledged global recession. \par \par \uc2  A change in the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  assumptions will automatically lead to the government adjusting its revenue and \b \highlight22\uc2 expenditure\b0 \highlight\uc2  targets. \par \par \uc2  In the original draft \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the government assumed a \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  of 2.5 percent of GDP. The revised version sees a \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  of 2.7 percent of GDP. \par \par \uc2  But as the government has accepted legislators demands for changes to the proposed revisions, the revised \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  remains tentative. \par \par \uc2  Legislators have demanded that the crude oil production assumption be increased by another 20,000 bpd over the government-proposed target. \par \par \uc2  This would translate into higher oil and gas revenues for the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which could alter the proposed \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  target. \par \par \uc2  Elsewhere, the government turned down legislators' demands that \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  be lowered. \par \par \uc2  Legislators argued that the high \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  were hampering the banks from resuming lending so as to spur \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth. \par \par \uc2  Minister of Finance Boediono, who attended the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  discussion, said the cost of adjusting the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  if \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  ended up higher next year was too expensive. \par \par \uc2  The government has tied a large portion of the interest on its bonds to \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020011009dxaa000bx\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw139\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2085\pichgoal600
