\par\par \b \uc2  IMF agrees to revised  \highlight22\uc2 budget \highlight\uc2  assumptions. \b0\par\par\uc2 578 \uc2 words\par \uc2 11 October 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  2 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  Berni K. Moestafa, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \par \uc2  The International Monetary Fund (IMF) has agreed to the revision of key assumptions in the 2002 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  draft, to ease Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  targets in the face of a global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recession. \par \par \uc2  "They (the IMF) don't object to the changes in the 2002 \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  assumptions," Minister of Finance Boediono said after a meeting with the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2 ' \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  committee. \par \par \uc2  The government and legislators agreed on Tuesday to a set of changes regarding the key assumptions for next year's state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The revisions followed new waves of \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  amid fears of a prolonged global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  downturn. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth, as measured by gross domestic product (GDP), was reduced to 4 percent from 5 percent, and the rupiah exchange rate against the U.S. dollar was lowered to 9,000 from 8,500. \par \par \uc2  Inflation was raised to 9 percent from 8 percent, while the \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  interest rate target was maintained at an average of 14 percent. \par \par \uc2  The oil production target, a large contributor to state revenue, was raised by 20,000 barrels per day (bpd) to 1.32 million bpd. Crude oil prices were maintained at US$22 a barrel. \par \par \uc2  The IMF dispatched a high level mission to Jakarta last week to review this year's state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  performance and next year's state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  outlook. \par \par \uc2  The team, which left the capital on Wednesday, said it saw no need to revise this year's \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  revenue targets, including those covered under the current Letter of Intent (LoI). \par \par \uc2  The LoI contains a set of reform targets the government must meet to obtain the IMF's aid. \par \par \uc2  Among the reform targets vital for the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  are the government's privatization and asset sales program. \par \par \uc2  The two revenue sources should help finance this year's \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which the government hopes to contain at 3.7 percent of GDP. \par \par \uc2  Asset sales have been progressing slowly and there have been no proceeds from privatization thus far. \par \par \uc2  The government has earmarked Rp 6.5 trillion (about US$650 million) in revenue from its privatization program this year. \par \par \uc2  Boediono acknowledged that the IMF had questioned the slow progress made in asset sales and privatization. \par \par \uc2  He said they advised the government to speed up efforts to achieve those targets. \par \par \uc2  To catch up on the \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  financing, he said that the government would ask for the disbursement of foreign loans that were still in the pipeline. \par \par \uc2  "There are some (loans) still pending, those from the World Bank, ADB (the Asian Development Bank) and probably also from Japan. \par \par \uc2  "We will request that the disbursement of these loans be expedited," he said, without remembering their total value. \par \par \uc2  The ADB is reportedly withholding a US$600 million loan tranche until the government has met the bank's preconditions. \par \par \uc2  Elsewhere, Citibank N.A. economist Anton Gunawan said the revised \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  assumptions were still too optimistic. \par \par \uc2  He said that the \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  interest rate next year would likely go higher than the average 14 percent targeted. \par \par \uc2  "There is too much pressure to raise \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," he said. \par \par \uc2  He said foreign debt payments, inflationary pressure from cuts in energy \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  and a weak rupiah reeling from domestic woes could prevent \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  from relaxing. \par \par \uc2  "We predict an average rupiah rate of about 10,000. Inflation is likely to come in at double digit rates, but slightly better than this year," Anton added. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020011011dxab00003\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
