\par\par \b \uc2  Emergency  \highlight22\uc2 budget \highlight\uc2  agenda. \b0\par\par\uc2 656 \uc2 words\par \uc2 19 October 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  4 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  The past six weeks must have been very taxing for the government and the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2 , especially the budgetary committee, as it has been deliberating the 2002 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  in a rapidly changing global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  environment. \par \par \uc2  Four days after the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  proposal had been submitted, the external factor - on which Indonesia's ailing \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  depends a great deal for its survival - was suddenly and radically changed by the September 11 terrorist attacks on the United States, the world's largest \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  deliberations certainly had to realign the focus of attention to a reassessment of the key assumptions used for the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  aggregates, otherwise the \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  plan would have been rejected by the market as entirely lacking in credibility. Remember the tragedy in early 1998 when then president Soeharto unveiled an unrealistic \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 ? The rupiah exchange rate collapsed from about Rp 4,000 to almost Rp 15,000 against the U.S. dollar. \par \par \uc2  Largely due to hard work and mutual understanding on the part of both parties about the urgency of the matter in their hands, the government and the House finally completed their tough, day-and-night debates and agreed on October 9 to change most of the key assumptions in the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The average rupiah exchange rate was changed from Rp 8,500 to Rp 9,000, inflation from 8 percent to 9 percent and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth from 5 percent to 4 percent. The average interest rate and crude oil price assumptions were maintained at 14 percent and US$22 per barrel respectively. These new assumptions, although still highly vulnerable due to the rapidly changing situation, seemed much more realistic than the original ones. \par \par \uc2  However, the deliberations seemed to have been bogged down by the other tough part of the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  - \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  allocations to the regional administrations. That is, understandably, still part of the learning curve, as the 2002 \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  will be only the second since the introduction of regional autonomy early this year. Many House members also seem to have been under strong pressure from the provinces they represent to lobby for larger appropriations. \par \par \uc2  The greatest danger, though, is that there is now a high risk of protracted debate delaying the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 's approval until December because the House will go into recess next Tuesday. \par \par \uc2  If that were the case, it would not only be fatal to sound \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  management but could also cause much chaos in the provinces, as they would not have had enough time to prepare their own budgets for implementation in January. Such an adverse situation could set off \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2 , social and political instability, as millions of civil servants could have to work without pay for one or two months. \par \par \uc2  Thus, we have reached yet another critical point in our multidimensional crisis, where the House is called upon to demonstrate its statesmanship by approving the 2002 \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  before its October 23 recess. \par \par \uc2  Central government's plan should be enacted at least two months before its implementation, to allow adequate time for provincial and district administrations to prepare their own budgets. These budgets, in contrast with what happened in the Soeharto era, will also still have to undergo tough debate within local legislatures. \par \par \uc2  Too much would be at stake if the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  were not approved by Monday, unless the House decided to demonstrate a higher sense of responsibility by postponing the start of its recess to the end of the month. \par \par \uc2  Whatever the case, the cost would be too great if the House stubbornly went into recess on Tuesday without first approving the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , as the delay would bring another kind of \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  into an already fragile situation. That, in turn, would render irrelevant the new key assumptions for the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which both the House and government had painstakingly worked out. \par \par \uc2  More devastating is that the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  could lose the small amount of confidence it still had in the House. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020011019dxaj00003\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
