 on a resolution this weekend to adopt pro-growth \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  and monetary policies. \par \par \uc2  Anwar said that base money had reached Rp 115.2 trillion at the end of September 2001, an increase of Rp 4.6 trillion on the level at the end of the second quarter. \par \par \uc2  He said that average growth in base money during the third quarter was 18.8 percent, compared to the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's average target of 11-12 percent. \par \par \uc2  He explained that the high base money growth was mainly due to strong liquidity demand by the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2 , driven by expectations of higher prices and continuing domestic political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  has forecast an inflation rate this year of 10 percent. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020011022dxak0000w\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw139\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2085\pichgoal600
