\par\par \b \uc2  WB URGES INDON GOV'T TO STICK TO TIGHT-MONEY  \highlight22\uc2 POLICY \highlight\uc2 . \b0\par\par\uc2 422 \uc2 words\par \uc2 5 November 2001\par \uc2 ANTARA - The Indonesian National News Agency\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 Asia Pulse Pte Limited. Asia Pulse gives no warranty or guarantee as to the accuracy of the information, Asia Pulse shall not be liable for errors or omissions in, or delays or interruptions to or cessation of delivery of, the data through its negligence or otherwise.\par \par \uc2  Jakarta, Nov 5 (ANTARA) - The World Bank (WB) has issued a recommendation to the Indonesian government to stick to the tight-money \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  until the end of the year in an effort to curb inflation. The recommendation was contained in a report on \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  development issued by the World Bank here Monday, ahead of the Consultative Group on Indonesia (CGI) meeting in Jakarta. In the CGI meeting on Nov 7-8, Indonesia will seek to get a new foreign aid amounting to US$ 3.7 billion. The WB report also cited recommendations on the sale of government assets in BCA Bank, Bank Niaga, and the Gresik cement factory, the sanctioning of an anti-money laundering law, the promotion of good governance, a rice supply \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  which weighs in balance the interests of farmers and consumers, and giving a sustained medium-term \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  role to the State Logistics Agency (Bulog). \par \par \uc2   Speaking in a press conference here Monday, WB senior economist, Vikram Nehru, pointed out that the Indonesian government has not achieved a significant headway in structural reform as well as in the implementation of good governance, thus instigating market confusion and uneasiness among donors and new creditors. Nehru also predicted lower \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth rates than those assumed by the Indonesian government for this year and the next. According to the WB economist, Indonesia's growth rate has been lagging behind those of East Asian countries, while more than half of its population are vulnerable to poverty. He said the unstable banking and business condition in Indonesia, coupled with worsening state finance, have made the country vulnerable to various risks which have direct impact on \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  sustainability. Nehru pointed out that the pressing priority that needs to be carried out by the Indonesian government is the promotion of \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  sustainability to ensure a stable \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth. According to him, in the run-up to the CGI meeting, the official creditors would exercise greater care in making commitments of support to the reform of policies if the government's track record has not given the required reasons to feel safe. He maintained that donor countries would adopt a realistic attitude in reviewing Indonesia's failure to overcome existing strong partisan interests, worsening structural weaknesses, the climate of \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  because of the decentralization program, and the strife-torn transition to democracy. Speaking about the privatization of state enterprises, Nehru advised the Indonesian government to overcome the problems involved to accelerate the realization of the program. \par \par \uc2 Document antara0020011107dxb5000bf\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  BI-40 index drop 2.17%. \b0\par\par\uc2 281 \uc2 words\par \uc2 5 November 2001\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA: Transaction activities of the blue chips last week remained \par \par \uc2  bearish. Market players continued to speculate selectively on the blue chips \par \par \uc2  almost throughout the week trading. \par \par \uc2  Th