\par\par \b \uc2  RUPIAH WEAKENS BY 115 POINTS IN TUESDAY MORNING'S SESSION. \b0\par\par\uc2 283 \uc2 words\par \uc2 6 November 2001\par \uc2 ANTARA - The Indonesian National News Agency\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 Asia Pulse Pte Limited. Asia Pulse gives no warranty or guarantee as to the accuracy of the information, Asia Pulse shall not be liable for errors or omissions in, or delays or interruptions to or cessation of delivery of, the data through its negligence or otherwise.\par \par \uc2  Jakarta, Nov 6 (ANTARA) - The Indonesian rupiah continued to weaken against the US dollar at Jakarta's inter-bank spot market on Tuesday morning, as a result of the lowering of Indonesia's long-term debts in Standard and Poor's international rating. \par \par \uc2  Until 10 a.m. on Tuesday, the rupiah was traded at Rp 10,945/Rp 10,970 to the dollar, weakening by 115 points from Monday's Rp 10,830/Rp 10,845. \par \par \uc2  "The negative sentiment is still apparent at the foreign exchange trading in the money market because of the lowering of Indonesia's long-term debts rating, from CCC+ to CCC. The pressure to sell the Indonesian currency has resulted in the strengthening of the US dollar, approaching Rp 11,000," commented a dealer from a private bank, who asked to remain anonymous. \par \par \uc2  According to him, in addition to the rating factor, the rupiah's bearish trend was also due to investors' increasing concern over the future of Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "The (Indonesian) \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which has yet to recover and is full of \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 , has influenced market players to safeguard their funds by converting them into US dollars," he said. \par \par \uc2  The accumulation of the negative sentiment at home has resulted in the market's failure to respond to the lowering of the \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  of the Fed funds by the US Federal Reserve Bank, the tenth in the current year, to 2 percent. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, in Asian money markets on Tuesday, the rates of the regional currencies to the dollar changed variably, while Japan's yen strengthened to 121.50 to the dollar from 121.75 on Monday. \par \par \uc2 Document antara0020011108dxb600001\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  On the eve of CGI meeting, World Bank expresses disappointment. \b0\par\par\uc2 585 \uc2 words\par \uc2 6 November 2001\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  Two days before the CGI meeting, the World Bank has criticized the government in reforming the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  under the IMF package, dismissing the efforts as a disappointment. \par \par \uc2  The Bank, in its report for the CGI meeting, said the government's first 100 days have not produced progress in terms of structural reforms and governance. \par \par \uc2  "The market is nervous while new creditors and donors are concerned," said the report that was submitted by the Bank's economist, Vikram Nehru. \par \par \uc2  The Bank noted that \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery slowed down even before the 11 September tragedy, a situation that was exacerbated by the slump in the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and the worsening of the investment climate in Indonesia. \par \par \uc2  This added more challenges to what the government is already facing, said the Bank. \par \par \uc2  "Political instability has raised social tension and slowed down \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reforms." \par \par \uc2  The report also noted that banking restructuring has slowed down and that many corporate debts remained unresolved. \par \par \uc2  "Corruption thrives, unpreventable due to the weak judicial system." \par \par \uc2  The report drove the rupiah to 11.000/US$, which was also due to the drop in the Indonesian debt rating from CCC+ to CCC by S&P. \par \par \uc2  The report, entitled "Reducing \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Vulnerability in Indonesia: The Imperative for Reform" was released two days before the Consultative Group for Indonesia meeting slated for 7-8 November in Jakarta. \par \par \uc2  An IMF team is scheduled to arrive in Jakarta to study the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  program, according to a press statement by the IMF yesterday, but would not prepare a new letter of intent. \par \par \uc2  If this week's CGI meeting and the IMF team visit proceed smoothly, the Paris Club is next year expected to provide debt relief to Indonesia. \par \par \uc2  The Bank said the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  would grow by 3,3% in 2001 and 3,5% in 2002, down from 4,8% in 2000. \par \par \uc2  The Bank said that while the Indonesian \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  is more robust than other crisis-hit Asian countries, its growth rate is still too low and lags behind its neighbors. \par \par \uc2  The banking and corporate sectors are weak while the government's financial matters are alarming, leaving Indonesia vulnerable to all kinds of risks, said the chairman of the CGI. \par \par \uc2  It said the priority is to ensure financial sustainability for the sake of stability as the basis for growth. \par \par \uc2  It noted that foreign gross financial support to cover the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  is US$7 billion, of which CGI would provide about US$3,0-3,5 billion. \par \par \uc2  It said that in reality in the past four years the \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  reached US$9 billion. \par \par \uc2  "Creditors are careful in committing themselves if the government's track record provides little reason for them to feel comfortable." \par \par \uc2  This year the CGI is committed to give US$4,8 billion, but only US$2,6 billion has so far been disbursed on the forms of program loans worth US$900 million and project loans worth US$1,7 billion, said the body. \par \par \uc2  It further said the 11 September tragedy underscored the need for reform, and that donors need to be realistic over what the government has so far achieved. \par \par \uc2  It noted that personal interests, weak institutions, \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  over decentralization, and unrest caused by the transition to democracy have undermined reforms. \par \par \uc2  The Bank said progress needs to be made in structural reforms, good governance, and empowerment and managing the poor, in line with the idea that stability, growth and effective governance are elements to reduce poverty. (m04/ab). \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020011107dxb600004\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
