\par\par \b \uc2  RI deserves CGI support - IMF. \b0\par\par\uc2 799 \uc2 words\par \uc2 7 November 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  Berni K. Moestafa, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \par \uc2  The International Monetary Fund (IMF) promised a helping hand in Indonesia's bid to secure some Rp 35.4 trillion (about US$3.7 billion) in new loans from the Consultative Group on Indonesia (CGI), as the Fund said it would suggest donor countries lend their support to Indonesia. \par \par \uc2  The IMF's senior resident representative in Jakarta, David C. Nellor said on Tuesday Indonesia deserved support from the CGI. \par \par \uc2  Although not a member of the group - which includes many donors from industrialized countries, the World Bank and the Asian Development Bank (ADB) - the IMF would present its view on the Indonesian \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  before participants of the CGI meeting, Nellor said. \par \par \uc2  "One of the elements (in the presentation) is the 2002 \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . It requires external financing, and we will argue that it deserves that support," he told reporters after a meeting with Coordinating Minister for the \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , Dorodjatun Kuntjoro-Jakti. \par \par \uc2  Nellor's statement came after the World Bank on Monday warned of increasingly wary donor countries, annoyed by Indonesia's poor track record in meeting reform targets. \par \par \uc2  The government hopes to secure some Rp 35.4 trillion in loans from the CGI, that would help it finance the \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the 2002 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  is estimated at Rp 42.1 trillion, which represents about 2.5 percent of the country's gross domestic product (GDP). \par \par \uc2  External financing from the CGI is expected to cover most of the gap, while domestic financing from privatization and asset sales should cover the balance. \par \par \uc2  According to Nellor, support from CGI members does exist. \par \par \uc2  Earlier last month, a senior government official told local newspapers that Japan was ready to pledge some US$1.4 billion, the World Bank some US$1 billion and the ADB between US$600 million to US$1 billion. \par \par \uc2  But thus far, none of the lenders confirmed the amount they would pledge during the CGI meeting. \par \par \uc2  The World Bank said the amount of its commitment depended on how the government was planning to use the funds. \par \par \uc2  "Donors will be interested in hearing what the government's plans are and how they propose to implement the various policies they've announced," Nellor explained. \par \par \uc2  He was referring to, among other things, the 2002 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which the World Bank previously described as sound and realistic. \par \par \uc2  "What people will be looking at is if there is a critical mass of policies which will enable the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  to grow," Nellor said. \par \par \uc2  He said meeting the donor countries would also allow the government to explain the challenges it faces in implementing reform programs. \par \par \uc2  And there is no shortage of challenges confronting the recently-installed government in its attempt to reform the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Privatization and asset sales targets, and the lack of action so far, are weighing heavily on foreign investors' appetite for Indonesian assets. \par \par \uc2  Chronic problems at home, ranging from anti-Western sentiment, legal \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 , and political instability, have dampened interest with regard to Indonesian companies. \par \par \uc2  Adding to this, is the accelerated downfall of the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  since the Sept. 11 terror strikes in the United States. \par \par \uc2  The entrance of foreign investors is vital to offset domestic investment, which has been sharply down since the financial crisis hit the country in 1997. \par \par \uc2  Investment from the private sector has become important, given the government's limited ability to stimulate \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth. \par \par \uc2  Massive debts cripple the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 's \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  ability, forcing the government to rely on private investors to drive the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Indonesia's total debt stands at some US$137.6 billion as of last August, of which US$74 billion is government debt. \par \par \uc2  Yet new loans from the CGI coupled with debt rescheduling under the Paris Club agreement are necessary to lend next year's \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  some degree of stability. \par \par \uc2  For this year's \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the significance of today's CGI meeting is to build confidence, according to a former IMF senior official. \par \par \uc2  Chairman of Deutsche Bank Asia, and former IMF Asia Pacific Deputy Director, Hubert Neiss said foreign investors use the CGI meeting to gauge Indonesia's reform progress. \par \par \uc2  "Private foreign investors still largely take a wait and see position....they will come a bit later, now is the time for official donors to support," Neiss told reporters in a press conference to introduce Deutsche Bank's new chief country officer, Suresh L. Narang. \par \par \uc2  A successful meeting of the CGI, he said, was bound to result in a confidence boost among foreign investors. \par \par \uc2  Analysts said regaining confidence was vital if the government hopes to succeed with its privatization and asset sales program this year. \par \par \uc2  This success rests largely on pushing ahead with the sale of PT Bank Central Asia (BCA) and cement company PT Semen Gresik. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020011107dxb70000j\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw139\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2085\pichgoal600
