\par\par \b \uc2  WB urges RI to restore confidence in 6 months. \b0\par\par\uc2 792 \uc2 words\par \uc2 8 November 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  Berni K. Moestafa, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \par \uc2  The World Bank urged the government on Wednesday to restore business confidence in this country within six months, as opportunities to revive that confidence was running out quickly. \par \par \uc2  The World Bank Vice President for the East Asia and Pacific Region, Jemal-ud-din Kassum said investor confidence had fallen sharply on the heels of a deteriorating global \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "We at the World Bank believe that Indonesia now has a narrow window of opportunity over the coming six months to restore that confidence." he said in his opening speech before participants of the Consultative Group on Indonesia's two-day meeting in Jakarta. \par \par \uc2  Kassum chairs the meeting of the CGI, which groups together Indonesia's major donor countries including multilateral donors such as the World Bank, and the Asian Development Bank (ADB). \par \par \uc2  Indonesia hopes to secure some Rp 35.4 trillion (about US$3.32 billion) in new loans from the CGI, to help finance next year's state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "This immediate opportunity needs to be seized urgently by Indonesia's political leaders to lock in macroeconomic stability, restore momentum to the \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  reform agenda and move decisively to reduce poverty and vulnerability," Kassum said. \par \par \uc2  Deteriorating confidence in the country's investment climate, has been a constant barrier to revitalizing the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  since it first plunged into crisis in 1997. \par \par \uc2  As a result, a World Bank report states that more than half of Indonesia's population of over 210 million have descended into poverty, living at less than $2 a day. \par \par \uc2  However, efforts to reverse this situation through \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth may rest more on the private sector than the government. \par \par \uc2  As \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  constraints limit government \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  capacity, the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  must turn to the private sector for growth. \par \par \uc2  Even within Indonesia, a weak banking sector withholding affordable funding sources, is causing domestic investment to run scarce. \par \par \uc2  For this reason instilling confidence among foreign investors is vital, according to the World Bank. \par \par \uc2  Kassum gave no explanation for his six-month timeframe, but made it clear that \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  on the global front are sure to cut short any confidence remaining among foreign investors. \par \par \uc2  "For the first time since the onset of the crisis, the huge domestic risks that Indonesia faces are now covered by a new layer of equally dangerous external risks," Kassum explained. \par \par \uc2  He was referring to the Sept. 11 terrorist attacks in the United States that accelerated the slump into a global recession. \par \par \uc2  In addition to a scarcity in foreign investments, the downturn also means a drop in export revenues, which last year, along with consumer \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2 , had kept the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  afloat. \par \par \uc2  According to the World Bank, one major barrier to the return of foreign investment was the country's weak legal system. \par \par \uc2  The issue of corruption tied to legal reforms formed part of the discussion in the CGI meeting for the first time. \par \par \uc2  In the past few years there have been a string of legal disputes involving foreign investors, which have had a negative impact on market sentiment. \par \par \uc2  "We will look closely at the justice sector, a major factor in the slow recovery of investment levels," Kassum said. \par \par \uc2  In response to the foreign criticism, Minister of Justice, Yusril Mahendra questioned foreign lenders' perceived double standard, stating that they show interest in legal consistency, but on the other hand there have been cases where foreigners, have interfered with legal proceedings to benefit one of their own companies. \par \par \uc2  "They sometimes try to use their political and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  influence to obstruct legal proceedings," he said in an apparent reference to a Canadian insurance company which had the government halt an investigation. \par \par \uc2  The government, he said, must refrain from meddling in legal proceedings, as it was asked to in the case of the Canadian-based life insurance firm PT Asuransi Jiwa Manulife Indonesia. \par \par \uc2  "I told them that this is a matter for an independent court," \par \par \uc2  Yet it is the court's independence, and lack of checks and balances, that has often been questioned by foreign investors. \par \par \uc2  The World Bank lambasted the country's judicial system as carrying a "systematic bias against foreign investors". \par \par \uc2  It said the impression among foreign investors was that acquiring assets from the government was difficult and risky. \par \par \uc2  2002 external financing needs and the CGI request \par \par \uc2  (US$ billion): \b \highlight22\uc2 Budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2 , 4.7; Domestic finance, 2.6; External finance needed, 2.1; Payment of external debts, 4.9; Total external financing needed, 7.0; Non CGI financing*, 3.7; CGI financing, 3.3; Total CGI financing requested, 3.3-3.5 \par \par \uc2  *Includes export credits as well as financing from other sources including the Paris Club reschedul