\par\par \b \uc2  Govt eyes fresh IMF loans this year. \b0\par\par\uc2 662 \uc2 words\par \uc2 13 November 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  2 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  Berni K. Moestafa, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \par \uc2  The government said it was upbeat about receiving an estimated US$400 million in new loans this year from the International Monetary Fund (IMF), based on the expectation that it would soon sign a new lending agreement with the Fund. \par \par \uc2  Finance minister Boediono said the government was in talks with a visiting IMF team for the drafting of a fourth Indonesia-IMF lending agreement, better known as a Letter of Intent (LoI). \par \par \uc2  "I'm optimistic because they (the IMF) will be staying here for about two weeks to review the LoI. But as we know, the disbursement will come after the LoI has been signed and approved," Boediono was quoted as saying by detik.com. \par \par \uc2  He forecast that the IMF would disburse its usual loan tranche of $400 million. \par \par \uc2  The IMF's loan tranche forms part of a $5 billion bail out package for Indonesia that is tied to a three-year \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reform program. \par \par \uc2  An IMF team arrived last week to review the current LoI and start discussions on the next one. Leading the team is the Fund's Senior Advisor for the Asia Pacific Department, Daniel Citrin. \par \par \uc2  So far, the government has signed three LoIs, the most recent one in August following an eight-month delay due to the slow progress of reforms. \par \par \uc2  Boediono said he was unsure whether the fourth LoI could be finalized within the next two weeks, reasoning that the talks were still at the preliminary stage. \par \par \uc2  "We'll complete our calculations and they (the IMF team) will bring the results back to Washington," he said. \par \par \uc2  "Then we can sign it (the LoI). About one or two weeks later it will be brought before the (IMF) committee for approval. Afterwards the loans can be disbursed," Boediono explained. \par \par \uc2  With less than two months left, the government is running short of funding to cover the \b \highlight22\uc2 expenditure\b0 \highlight\uc2  targets set out in this year's state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  As a result, the government is looking at a mushrooming \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which was initially set at 3.7 percent of gross domestic product (GDP). \par \par \uc2  Constraints on the 2001 \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  are one concern of the IMF team in its review of the current LoI, Boediono said. \par \par \uc2  The government's lagging behind in its privatization and asset disposal program threatens to cut short domestic \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  financing. \par \par \uc2  As yet, privatization proceeds have amounted to zero, while progress in asset sales is impeded by a sluggish market. \par \par \uc2  Elsewhere, external \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  financing is facing the axe due to loan preconditions the government cannot meet on time. \par \par \uc2  According to the World Bank, the undisbursed loans amount to about $900 million of the $2.6 billion pledged by creditor nations. \par \par \uc2  It remains unclear whether the government can unlock the loans through efforts to persuade lenders to ease some of the preconditions. \par \par \uc2  Short on receipts, the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  is also seeing a surge in \b \highlight22\uc2 expenditure\b0 \highlight\uc2 , partly as the weaker rupiah drives up the cost of servicing interest on domestic and foreign debts. \par \par \uc2  By contrast, \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  collection is moving in line with \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  targets, according to government officials. \par \par \uc2  The outlook for the oil and gas sector remains \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2 , however. \par \par \uc2  "If oil prices continue to fall, we won't have any more windfall profits," the president of the state oil and gas company Pertamina, Baihaki Hakim, told reporters. \par \par \uc2  This year's \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  assumed an average oil price of $24 per barrel. As of October, the price stood at $25 per barrel, he said. \par \par \uc2  However, the profit margin of $1 per barrel comes at the cost of a lower than expected oil production level. \par \par \uc2  "The \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  assumed an oil production level of 1.46 million barrels per day (bpd), but we've been able to produce only 1.3 million bpd," Baihaki explained. \par \par \uc2  The IMF said last week that the government may need to resort to \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  cuts if it runs out of funding sources. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020011112dxbd000b5\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  BRI optimistic to enter bourse by 2002. \b0\par\par\uc2 357 \uc2 words\par \uc2 13 November 2001\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  The management of PT Bank Rakyat Indonesia is \par \par \uc2  optimistic \par \par \uc2  it can hold an IPO by the end of 2002 but would remain cautious on the \par \par \uc2  development of the banking sector following \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and \par \par \uc2  political \par \par \uc2  conditions. \par \par \uc2  Head of Retail Division of BRI Suwardi Saropie said the bank's 2001 \par \par \uc2  performance supports the IPO (initial \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  offering) plan, especially \par \par \uc2  in \par \par \uc2  terms of retail credit extension growth. "BRI's retail sector has been \par \par \uc2  able \par \par \uc2  to extend 80% of the total credits provided, and per September 2001, we \par \par \uc2  have \par \par \uc2  already extended Rp4 trillion of the Rp5 trillion target," said Suwardi \par \par \uc2  over \par \par \uc2  the weekend. \par \par \uc2  According to him, with such performance, the IPO plan would become the \par \par \uc2  bank's main agenda, which focuses on training and developments of the \par \par \uc2  small \par \par \uc2  and medium enterprises sector. But he added that BRI would also watch \par \par \uc2  the \par \par \uc2  developments in the country, especially the banking sector, which is \par \par \uc2  once \par \par \uc2  again hit by confidence crisis due to requirement to reach the 8% CAR \par \par \uc2  (capital adequacy ratio). The 8% CAR has to be met by the end of the \par \par \uc2  year \par \par \uc2  and in 2002, the banking sector is expected to reach a 12% CAR target. \par \par \uc2  He said that such requirement is potential to further bring down the \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2 's trusts on the national banking sector and could even affect \par \par \uc2  the \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2 's enthusiasm on BRI's IPO. But for certain, BRI as of early 2003 \par \par \uc2  will \par \par \uc2  start to make an all out improvements, both on the operational system \par \par \uc2  and \par \par \uc2  extension schemes of the credit products launched, said Suwardi. \par \par \uc2  In the meantime, Deputy Chief of East Java BRI office Heru Sukanto said \par \par \uc2  regional claims on retail commercial credit as per September 2001 is \par \par \uc2  now at \par \par \uc2  3.91% from a total of Rp2.2 trillion credit extended. \par \par \uc2  "The extension target of retail credits in the East Java region is 61%, \par \par \uc2  it \par \par \uc2  has already reached 59% per August 2001," he said in his office. \par \par \uc2  The East Java BRI data showed that from a total of Rp6.1 trillion \par \par \uc2  credit \par \par \uc2  extended, the retail sector absorbed 37%, the micro sector 26%, medium \par \par \uc2  sector 24%, and corporation 13%. (maj). \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020011113dxbd00003\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  Indef, Econit projections -  \highlight22\uc2 Economy \highlight\uc2  2002 gloomy. \b0\par\par\uc2 306 \uc2 words\par \uc2 15 November 2001\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  Two independent think tanks - Indef and Econit-have said that the Indonesian \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  in 2002 would be gloomy, growing by 2.68% due to constraints in the recovery process. \par \par \uc2  Indef said the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  would grow by about 2%, while Econit predicted a 3%-4% growth. \par \par \uc2  Economist of Indef Dradjad Wibowo blamed the low figure on \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  over key issues, including the APBN (state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 ). \par \par \uc2  Indef, said Dradjad, found the figure of 2.86% quite optimistic, and predicted the price of oil would be US$19 per barrel. \par \par \uc2  Econit, said Rizal Ramli, predicted that the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  would in 2002 grow by 3.5%-4%, as our exports have weakened due to the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  slump. \par \par \uc2  Econit said exports in 2002 would slow down drastically, growing by 13%, while imports would grow only by 15% in 2001 and 2002. \par \par \uc2  "In the past three years, the engine of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  development was domestic demand. If that could be maintained, we could just grow by 4%," he said. \par \par \uc2  Econit also said that Megawati Soekarnoputri Cabinet's ability to reform the laws, politics, and the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  is crucial to seeing higher growth after 2002, as it is subject to foreign direct investment (FDI). \par \par \uc2  Without FDI, said Econit, the long-term \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth figure would be 4%-6%. \par \par \uc2  It also predicted that the \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  in APBN 2001 would be 5.29% of the GDP. \par \par \uc2  Indef has urged the government to allocate only Rp30 trillion to pay off debts, and set a ceiling on new loans at US$2-2.5 billion a year. \par \par \uc2  "This would ease the pressure on the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 's \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2 ." \par \par \uc2  Econit also urged BI to ease monetary policies in order to stimulate the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , as high inflation is caused more by rising fuel prices and electricity tariffs, and not other monetary factors. (m04/aph). \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020011116dxbf0005m\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
