\par\par \b  \highlight22\uc2 Economy \highlight\uc2  grew 3.47% in third quarter - BPS. \b0\par\par\uc2 463 \uc2 words\par \uc2 16 November 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  24 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  Adianto P. Simamora, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \par \uc2  The Central Bureau of Statistics (BPS) reported on Thursday that the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , as measured by gross domestic product (GDP), grew by 3.47 percent in the third quarter of this year compared to the same period last year. \par \par \uc2  BPS said that, compared to the second quarter, GDP grew by 2.8 percent. \par \par \uc2  BPS chief Soedarti Surbakti said that full-year GDP growth would be in line with the government's target of 3.5 percent. \par \par \uc2  "With the third quarter performance, we are optimistic GDP growth will reach at least 3.5 percent this year," Surbakti said. \par \par \uc2  Some analysts had earlier predicted that 2001 \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth would be below the government target, primarily due to the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  slump worsened by the Sept. 11 terrorist attacks on the U.S.. \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  slowdown in developed countries, particularly the U.S. and Japan, will affect Indonesia's exports, because they were major markets influencing last year's 4.8 percent \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth. \par \par \uc2  BPS said that, based on current prices, GDP was equal to Rp 1,101.4 trillion, while based on 2000 constant prices, GDP was Rp 1,290.7 trillion. \par \par \uc2  BPS said that the third quarter GDP growth was contributed to by consumption, government \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  and exports. \par \par \uc2  BPS said that consumption grew by 7.12 percent in the third quarter compared to the same period last year, and 3.43 percent compared to the second quarter of this year. \par \par \uc2  The bureau said that government \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  increased by 11.86 percent in the third quarter year-on-year, and 1.43 percent quarter-on-quarter. \par \par \uc2  It said that, while exports grew by 6.57 percent in the third quarter compared to the same period last year, they contracted by 7.13 percent when compared to the second quarter. \par \par \uc2  The drop in export performance reflected the fact that the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  slump had affected the country's export sector. \par \par \uc2  BPS also said that investment activities dropped by 4.3 percent year-on-year, and 7.6 percent quarter-on-quarter. \par \par \uc2  The drop in investment activity is related to the ongoing \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  problems at home, with the banking sector reluctant to provide credit and the prospect of slower export performance amid the global slump. \par \par \uc2  BPS also reported that business confidence in the fourth quarter was expected to decline due to various \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The bureau's business confidence index between July and September this year stood at 105.36 points. \par \par \uc2  A reading above 100 means businesses are still optimistic about the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , while below 100 indicates pessimism. \par \par \uc2  BPS deputy chief Kusmadi Saleh said that the index for the fourth quarter of this year may drop to 98.97. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020011116dxbg0000l\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
