\par\par \b \uc2  TUESDAY'S EDITORIALS IN INDONESIA'S MAJOR DAILIES. \b0\par\par\uc2 649 \uc2 words\par \uc2 20 November 2001\par \uc2 ANTARA - The Indonesian National News Agency\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 Asia Pulse Pte Limited. Asia Pulse gives no warranty or guarantee as to the accuracy of the information, Asia Pulse shall not be liable for errors or omissions in, or delays or interruptions to or cessation of delivery of, the data through its negligence or otherwise.\par \par \uc2  EXTENDING IMF PROGRAM \par \par \uc2  If securing another debt rescheduling package is the primary motive behind the Indonesian government's request for the International Monetary Fund (IMF) to extend its program for one year, reform efforts in the country will never be able to achieve the level capable of generating sustainable \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery even after 2003. \par \par \uc2  True, debt rescheduling alone is already a compelling reason. The government may default on its US$74 billion foreign debts if it cannot get another rescheduling deal from the Paris Club of sovereign creditors at least for debt principals maturing between April 2002 and March 2004. Since the Paris Club deal is tied to a borrower's conformity with IMF programs, the government needs to extend the IMF facility, which is scheduled to expire in December 2002, at least for another year. \par \par \uc2  However, a one-year extension would not be effective for building stronger foundations for sustainable recovery if the government and the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of\b0 \highlight\b \highlight22\uc2 Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  did not augment their cooperation in grasping the nettle of reform. \par \par \uc2  Therefore, the House, which has often criticized the IMF for what it sees as escessive intervention in Indonesia's sovereignity, should support the government's request for and extension of the IMF program. Despite its shortcomings, IMF involvement is required to maintain international creditors' commitment to the country. The current IMF program could be the last chance for the country to secure a sustainable \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery. - The Jakarta Post (T008) \par \par \uc2  WAITING FOR A MEETING AMONG PARTIES' ELITE \par \par \uc2  Rumors have lately spread that poor relations among cabinet \par \par \uc2  ministers and the bureaucracy has resulted in weak decisions. \par \par \uc2  Not only the bureaucracy, the government and the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of\b0 \highlight\par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  have often had unnecessary differences in opinions. \par \par \uc2  There are so many problems.  But if we observe it carefully, the \par \par \uc2  question is more about the need for the political elite to agree on how to manage the country so that they would be able to lead it out of the crisis. - Bisnis Indonesia (T008/c/h-cvl/c/b003) 2.11:55 \par \par \uc2  WELCOME THE OCEAN OF \b \highlight22\uc2 UNCERTAINTIES\b0 \highlight\par \par \uc2  Recession has hit the world \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which is facing \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the future. The attacks on the World Trade Center and the Pentagon are the strongest sources of these \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  We in Indonesia have undoubtedly been affected since we are \par \par \uc2  catagorized as a poor country. \par \par \uc2  We, however, must face these \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 .  Thus, the Megawati \par \par \uc2  government must have a clear vision on \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .  But three months \par \par \uc2  into her administration, we have not yet seen her \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  vision. \par \par \uc2  Where are we going then?  We do not have any certain destination. \par \par \uc2  Amid the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the world \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , we have to work. \par \par \uc2  We need to have clear visions on where to direct our \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . We have to make priorities and implement them. - Republika (T008/c/h-cvl/c/b003) 2.12:02 \par \par \uc2  ENDING THE STUPID SANTA CLAUS ROLE \par \par \uc2  The government has finally decided on how to settle the case of 11 ailing banks under the Indonesian Bank Restructuring Agency. \par \par \uc2  Only one or two banks will be allowed to do their business as \par \par \uc2  usual, the rest will be merged. \par \par \uc2  The question is, until when will the government play Santa Claus \par \par \uc2  to these banks?  The government has allowed bank owners whose banks \par \par \uc2  had gone bankrupt, to stay free. \par \par \uc2  Where is the law?  Where is justice?  The government, including \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 , whether deliberately or not, has protected these \par \par \uc2  robbers hiding behind the honored institution called the bank. \par \par \uc2  There are two big tasks the government must carry out.  First, \par \par \uc2  the government has to bring them to court as \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  criminals. Second, the government should take strong actions so it can continue to keep ailing banks. \par \par \uc2  A bank needs trust and so does the government. This social trust will disappear if the government chooses to act like Santa Claus in protecting these ailing banks. - Media Indonesia. \par \par \uc2 Document antara0020011122dxbk0005r\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
