\par\par \b \uc2  Govt to complete key talks with IMF today. \b0\par\par\uc2 579 \uc2 words\par \uc2 20 November 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  Dadan Wijaksana and Berni K. Moestafa, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \par \uc2  After weeks of intense discussion, the government and the visiting International Monetary Fund (IMF) mission team are expected to complete the assessment of the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  condition and reform programs on Tuesday. \par \par \uc2  "(The discussion) has been going well, but it's not finalized just yet. We'll still have a chance to meet tomorrow, we'll wrap it up all by then," Finance Minister Boediono told reporters late on Monday following a meeting between key \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  ministers and the IMF team. \par \par \uc2  He declined to provide further details. \par \par \uc2  A special mission of the IMF, led by the Fund's senior adviser for the Asia Pacific department Daniel Citrin, has been in Jakarta for two weeks not only to review the country's latest \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  condition, but also together with the government to draft Indonesia's fourth letter of intent (LoI). \par \par \uc2  The LoI, in this case, is a set of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  targets and reform programs which must be achieved and implemented by the government within a certain period of time to qualify for further loans under the IMF's structural adjustment program. \par \par \uc2  The draft of the LoI will be brought to the IMF board of directors in Washington for approval, which will pave the way for the disbursement of the Fund's next US$400 million loan tranche. \par \par \uc2  The government expects the IMF to make the next loan disbursement later this year. The disbursement of the IMF money is crucial to help revive investor confidence in the ailing \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Indonesia has so far received around $1.2 billion out of the $5 billion loan program agreed upon in late 1999. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, State Minister of State Enterprises Laksamana Sukardi also confirmed the smooth process of the discussions, saying that so far there had been nothing that could lead to any disagreement. \par \par \uc2  Among the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  targets set for the fourth LoI, according to sources, were an \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth target of 3-4 percent for 2002, inflation of 9-10 percent and Rp 42.5 trillion ($4 billion) proceeds from the sale of assets under the Indonesian Bank Restructuring Agency (IBRA). \par \par \uc2  Earlier, a \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  (BI) senior official said that one important item to be included in the LoI was a plan to launch a new investigation into alleged misuse of some Rp 138.4 trillion in BI emergency loans. \par \par \uc2  The case centers around the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's liquidity support to 48 local banks during the peak of the 1997 financial crisis. \par \par \uc2  Although two separate investigations have been conducted in the case, they yielded neither prosecutions nor the repayment of the loans. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, regional banking analyst Lin Che Wei at SG Securities warned the move might stir legal \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  for debtors under IBRA. \par \par \uc2  "The implications of this (probe) can spread everywhere," he told The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2  Any follow-up on the probe will inevitably lead to reviewing IBRA's Master of Settlement and Acquisition Agreements (MSAA) - a deal requiring bank owners to surrender assets to IBRA as collateral for their debts to the government. \par \par \uc2  He said forcing debtors to transfer more assets despite the MSAA, would hurt debtors' rights guaranteed in that document. \par \par \uc2  Che Wei said the government should realize that the loan abuse case may not get resolved within a short time. It must also know the consequences if this were to become an item on the next LoI. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020011119dxbk000mw\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
