\par\par \b \uc2  Domestic  \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties \highlight\uc2  to cloud Indonesia Recovery Fund - Expert. \b0\par\par\uc2 460 \uc2 words\par \uc2 26 November 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  20 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \par \uc2  The government will face difficulties attracting sufficient foreign funds into the planned Indonesian Recovery Fund due to various domestic \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 , according to one \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  expert. \par \par \uc2  Gadjah Mada University (UGM) economist Sri Adiningsih said on Sunday that slow progress in the implementation of the country's key \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reform programs, legal \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  and security problems would deter investors from participating in the fund. \par \par \uc2  "I doubt that the fund can be as successful as the one in Thailand. There's just too many \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  here," Sri said. \par \par \uc2  She pointed out that the government's failure to sell a majority stake in the state-owned cement producer PT Semen Gresik to Mexican giant Cemex SA as scheduled was a major blow to foreign investor confidence in the country. \par \par \uc2  Minister of Industry and Trade Rini Soewandi announced on Friday that the government would launch an Indonesian Recovery Fund early next year in a bid to attract foreign funds to help revive the country's anemic real sector and create jobs. \par \par \uc2  Rini said that the fund would be similar to one established in Thailand, which managed to raise around US$1.6 billion in cash from well known institutions such as the Asian Development Bank (ADB), the World Bank's investment arm the International Finance Corporation, and Merryl Lynch. \par \par \uc2  She said that initial funding levels for the Indonesian Recovery Fund were expected to reach $200 million, with some $10 million to come from the government. \par \par \uc2  "The government can just go ahead with the plan, but the main issue here is how to resolve the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  created by structural (\b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2 ) and security problems," Sri said. \par \par \uc2  Sri said that the various \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  had even triggered a massive capital outflow that, according to a recent report quoting \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  senior deputy governor Anwar Nasution, had reached an average of $10 billion per annum since the country plunged into a combination of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and political crises in 1998. \par \par \uc2  "If the government could manage to at least reduce the capital outflow, it would already be a significant contribution to the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," she said. \par \par \uc2  Separately, a business association executive, who requested anonymity, also doubted the ability of the government to attract foreign financial institutions to invest in the recovery fund given the IFC's bad experience dealing with the local legal system. \par \par \uc2  "I doubt the IFC will agree to chip in," he said. \par \par \uc2  The IFC failed to force PT Panca Overseas Finance Indonesia (POFI) into bankruptcy over $13 million in unresolved debts after the commercial court ruled in favor of POFI. \par \par \uc2  Very few creditors have been able to book victories in bankruptcy cases since the country's new bankruptcy law was enacted in 1998. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020011126dxbq0000i\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
