\par\par \b \uc2  MONDAY'S EDITORIALS OF INDONESIA'S MAJOR DAILIES. \b0\par\par\uc2 735 \uc2 words\par \uc2 3 December 2001\par \uc2 ANTARA - The Indonesian National News Agency\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 Asia Pulse Pte Limited. Asia Pulse gives no warranty or guarantee as to the accuracy of the information, Asia Pulse shall not be liable for errors or omissions in, or delays or interruptions to or cessation of delivery of, the data through its negligence or otherwise.\par \par \uc2  LAW HELD IN CONTEMPT \par \par \uc2  The way our legal system has bungled the Tommy Soeharto affair has sent a chilling message that, not only does crime in this country pay, but that if you ever find yourself on the wrong side of the law, it pays to evade the law altogether. Judging from Tommy's case, you're not going to be worse off if you are ever arrested after escaping from the law. It's certainly worth a try. \par \par \uc2  Until his arrest on Wednesday, businessman Hutomo Mandala Putra, the son of former president Soeharto, had eluded the law on more than one count. Now that he has been nabbed, the police do not appear to have the slightest intention of punishing the billionaire businessman for evading the law. Police are only questioning Tommy in connection with the murder of judge M. Syaifuddin Kartasasmita, illegal possession of firearms, and a series of bombings in Jakarta. \par \par \uc2      Tommy's latest escape from the corruption charge is another \par \par \uc2  illustration of how messy our legal system is. \par \par \uc2      Tomy was first acquitted by the South Jakarta District Court of \par \par \uc2  a corruption charge in the Goro-Bulog land case. \par \par \uc2      The Goro-Bulog case has been overturned so many times that it is \par \par \uc2  no longer a question of seeking truth and justice, which admittedly must be an endless process. The Tommy Soeharto affair has now become nothing more than a legal play thing. This is a travesty of the law that has created even more \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  about the legal system in this country. - The Jakarta Post \par \par \uc2  YEAR-END OPTIMISM \par \par \uc2  The latest data issued by the Central Bureau of Statistics (BPS) shows that trade surplus during the January-October period this year stood at US$ 21.4 billion. \par \par \uc2  The figure is lower than that of last year which reached US$ 25 billion, but considering the decreasing price of oil in the world market, this achievement should please us. \par \par \uc2  The country also earned more money last month from the selling of some assets of publicly-listed PT Indosiar Visual Mandiri and Riau Industrial Estates as well as the repayment of \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  emergency liquidity support (BLBI) worth Rp 14.8 trillion by publicly-listed Bank Danamon Indonesia. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, the government agreed to sell all assets of PT Semen Gresik to Mexican investor, Cemex, at a price of US$ 200 million but maintain assets of PT Semen Padang and PT Tonasa. \par \par \uc2      Another good news is the arrest of fugitive Hutomo "Tommy" \par \par \uc2  Mandala Putra last week. \par \par \uc2      The progress in the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and judicial sectors will not \par \par \uc2  immediately end the prolonged \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis in Indonesia, but at least it can give us new hope that with very serious efforts, the country would be free from the crisis in the next few years. -Bisnis Indonesia \par \par \uc2  A SUPERCOMPETENT INSTITUTION \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  (DPR) has almost forgotten its function. Legislators seem to have forgotten their tasks and consider the House a super institution. They are taking care of all businesses but are ignoring their own tasks, while hiding behind the grand ideas of transparency and \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  accountability. \par \par \uc2  The DPR has enthusiastically worked on its supervisory function. Ironically however, many of its improper moves need to be supervised. \par \par \uc2  The latest case is the trip to Germany by legislators to visit a ship-maker which will participate in a tender for the state-run shipping company, PT Pelni. This is weird because legislators have acted like ticket scalpers who are incompetent for their position. \par \par \uc2  The tendency for DPR to meddle in a company's micro issues has grown. There is no more limit between management's authority which should be accounted to shareholders, and \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  competence which need to be disclosed by ministers to the House. The DPR is a supercompetent institution. \par \par \uc2  The DPR's function has changed. Once it was a base for hoodlums because its members were fighting each other. At one time, it was a showroom for luxury cars parked outside its building. Recently, it became a station full of ticket scalpers because its members intervened in the micro issues of state companies. \par \par \uc2  We have seen odd attitudes in the House. It is weird, because it is tacky, improper and a crime, but on the other hand, it feels it is the most powerful institution. The worst part is that legislators do not feel that something has gone wrong. - Media Indonesia. \par \par \uc2 Document antara0020011205dxc300004\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
